    <Placemark>
        <name>NO KINGS, NO ICE Cicero-Berwyn</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS, NO ICE Cicero-Berwyn</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Cicero Town Hall<br>4949 W Cermak Rd<br>Cicero, IL 60804</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us in the streets March 28 to say NO KINGS and NO ICE RAIDS in our communities!  

The action will be centered in Cicero and Berwyn, two majority Latino suburbs of Chicago that have been hit extremely hard by the ICE offensive  known as Operation Midway Blitz.  We expect to be hit even harder in the spring.  Our rally will focus on standing up to ICE raids, and countering the fear that has gripped our two communities.   

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904783/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
