        <name>Join NO KINGS 3 Rally/Protest - ARLINGTON HEIGHTS, IL, Saturday, Mar 28@10am-Noon  @Clock Tower</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Join NO KINGS 3 Rally/Protest - ARLINGTON HEIGHTS, IL, Saturday, Mar 28@10am-Noon  @Clock Tower</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Arlington Heights Clock Tower<br>153 E Northwest Hwy<br>Arlington Heights, IL 60004</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>### Join NO KINGS 3 Rally / Protest in ARLINGTON HEIGHTS, IL, Saturday, March 28th 10am -Noon  @Clock Tower Plaza

_Join us for the Arlington Height, IL Rally/Protest “NO Kings 3” - Saturday, March 28 @10 am at the SW corner of Arlington Heights Road and Highway 14 in Arlington Heights for a ** Protest Trump / Trump Administration Unconstitutional Actions**. 

Enjoy music, bagpiping, meeting other folks, enter the best costume contest by the 34’ tall Trump Chicken at 11:15, and much much more!!

This peaceful, visible action will call attention to the Trump Administration Unconstitutional Actions, ICE Actions, and the escalating abuses being carried out in our name. We will gather as a community to demand accountability and to insist that every person’s life and dignity be respected._

#### Let us know you will be Attending Saturday’s “NO KINGS 3” March 28th 10-12 .. RSVP HERE -&gt; https://mobilize.us/s/a0CZ79

#### to Volunteer to help for the AH NK 3: 

 - For general help please show up at 9 am to assist with signs and chicken and general set up and possible manning a table..

 - For being a Safely Marshall ..  show up at 9:30 and meet with the Safety Lead Robert at the 34’ Tall Chicken by the Clock Tower for instructions, Safety Vest and Walkie Talkies

#### Please RSVP here to volunteer -&gt;  https://mobilize.us/s/liAgZm

#### CO-HOSTS:

 - NWSOFA-INDIVISIBLE (NorthWest Suburbs (Chicago) Organizing for Action ..an Indivisible Chapter

- Indivisible Illinois

 - Wheeling Township Democrats

 - Greater Palatine Area Democrats

 - Young Democrats of Wheeling Township

 - Hands Off Wheeling

 - We Volunteer - NW Suburbs

 - Progressive Palatine 

#### All are welcome—new volunteers, longtime activists, families, and community members who are just now getting engaged. 

_Bring signs, friends, and your passion for justice. Dress for the weather and be prepared for a peaceful, nonviolent action. Together, we can shine a light on injustice, build solidarity, and make it clear that our community rejects cruelty, impunity, and dangerous extremism in all its forms._

A core principle behind all ICE Out For Good events is a commitment to nonviolent action and no civil disobedience. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values, and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events. All events should be held in public spaces or on public property.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/924970/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
