    <Placemark>
        <name>Stop ICE-No Kings-Hands Off-Rally for Democracy</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stop ICE-No Kings-Hands Off-Rally for Democracy</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Highway of Flags Veterans Memorial<br>SE Corner of U.S. 41 and Ridge Road<br>Highland, IN 46322</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible NWI</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We rally every Saturday, 12-1. We’ve partnered with veterans groups to fight for democracy and all our rights every week. We’ll be in Highland on the SE corner of Ridge and 41 at the Highway of Flags Veterans Memorial. Limited parking, along with handicapped spots, is available behind the memorial. If the lot is full, park at Wicker Park and rally on the NW corner of Ridge and 41. Or park in the old Ultra parking lot and rally on the NE corner. Bring your signs and your passion! And please bring nonperishable food items. We donate to a different pantry each week.

There are no bathrooms at the Memorial. There are restrooms at Wicker Park on Ridge Rd. and at the Highland Public Library, 2841 Jewett Ave.

Please note, we are joining the National No Kings Day on March 28. The event will be 12-2-with speakers, music &amp; rallying. We expect a large crowd. There will be plenty of yellow vested volunteers on hand to help and provide security.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/862582/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
