    <Placemark>
        <name>People&apos;s Patrol Training at Casa Dupage</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>People&apos;s Patrol Training at Casa Dupage</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 27, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Casa Dupage Workers Center<br>311 S Naperville Rd<br>Wheaton, IL 60187</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Come Join the People&apos;s Patrol Grassroots Rapid Response Network! The People&apos;s Patrol is the leading grassroots rapid response in Chicagoland- based on the values of direct action, horizontalism and mutual aid, the People&apos;s Patrol represents over 400 patrollers in the Chicagoland area. Join us for a training to join the patrol and further the defense of your community from ICE while through democracy and solidarity, lay the bases for a new society! 

WE will meet at Casa Dupage Workers Center, 311 S. Naperville Rd. Wheaton for a training to prepare us to patrol our communities! Friday, February 27, 5pm-7pm, in Spanish and English!  

************************************************

Across the country, communities are organizing to disentangle local law enforcement from federal immigration enforcement. When local police or sheriffs collaborate with ICE, it undermines trust, separates families, and makes all of us less safe.

***Our goal is simple and clear:***
No local resources for ICE. No contracts. No data-sharing. No collaboration.

At this event, we will:

1. Bring together neighbors, workers, and allies
2. Prepare to meet with local elected officials (or attend a public meeting)
3. Call on our [city/county/state] leaders to move forward policies that disentangle ICE from local law enforcement

Take concrete steps toward passing local protections

This effort builds on years of organizing led by immigrant communities nationwide — from the fight against 287g contracts to the sanctuary victories that have proven local action works. Cities and states that say NO to ICE are a critical bulwark against mass deportations and the erosion of civil rights.

There is much that we can do locally. And there is much that our elected officials can do — if we demand courage and leadership. Join us!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/910803/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
