        <name>SIGNS OF FASCISM MARCH | Saugatuck | Hosted by: Good Trouble Indivisible</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>SIGNS OF FASCISM MARCH | Saugatuck | Hosted by: Good Trouble Indivisible</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, May 23, 2026 at 3:30 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Saugatuck Town Hall<br>102 Butler St<br>Saugatuck, MI 49453</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>GOOD TROUBLE INDIVISIBLE

SIGNS OF FASCISM &amp; ICE OUT FOR GOOD 
— Silent March for Democracy —

PLEASE REGISTER FOR THIS EVENT.

We need a strong turnout to make this action visible in our community.

Watch our marches here:
SIGNS OF FASCISM March:
https://www.facebook.com/share/v/1GLi2oqvqT/

ICE OUT FOR GOOD March:
https://www.facebook.com/share/r/1ATArSfNpB/

⸻

⏰ 11:30 AM — ARRIVE &amp; SIGN IN
Look for Jan’s YELLOW JEEP to sign in and pick up your sign.

⏰ 11:45 AM — LINE UP
Photo opportunity, marching instructions, safety guidance, and route overview.

⏰ NOON — MARCH BEGINS

Participants will walk silently through downtown in a disciplined, peaceful visibility march.

Dress code: All black

A slow heartbeat drum sets the pace.

No chanting.

No shouting.

No confrontation.

Just a clear and powerful public witness.

⸻

THE MARCH

The first lap through downtown represents our SIGNS OF FASCISM march.

Participants walk single file carrying stark black-and-white signs identifying warning signs of authoritarianism appearing in America today.

The second lap represents ICE OUT FOR GOOD — a call for accountability, human rights, and the rule of law.

All signs are provided.

This is a nonviolent public awareness action designed to make people stop, notice, and think about the direction of our country.

⸻

WHY WE SHOW UP

Democracy does not defend itself.

It survives because ordinary people refuse to look away.

Every person who shows up makes this action stronger.

Join us.

Be visible.

Be counted.

Be Good Trouble.

⸻

ABOUT GOOD TROUBLE INDIVISIBLE

Good Trouble Indivisible (GTI) is a Saugatuck and Douglas–based grassroots advocacy organization committed to nonviolent action, democratic accountability, and the defense of human rights.

GTI has organized more than 130 public actions across West Michigan.

We show up — week after week — to defend democracy and the right to peaceful protest.

⸻

VOLUNTEER OPPORTUNITY

Want to help organize actions like this?

Many volunteer roles can be done from home.

Call or text Jan Cohen at (269) 932-8806
or email Action@GoodTroubleIndivisible.org

⸻

☎️ (616) 287-2221

📧 Action@GoodTroubleIndivisible.org

🌐 GoodTroubleIndivisible.org (launching soon)


A core principle of all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. Participants are expected to de-escalate any potential confrontation.</p>
