        <name>THE CONVERSATION | Saugatuck-Douglas | Hosted by Good Trouble Indivisible</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>THE CONVERSATION | Saugatuck-Douglas | Hosted by Good Trouble Indivisible</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 29, 2026 at 9:30 PM UTC - 10:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>THE MEETING ROOM<br>252 Grand St<br>Saugatuck, MI 49453</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Good Trouble Indivisible Presents:  THE CONVERSATION

📍 THE MEETING ROOM – A Space for Collective Voice 

252 Grand St, Saugatuck, MI 49453

📆 Every Sunday Evening 

⏰ 5:30 PM – 6:30 PM 

Event Description:

THE CONVERSATION is a community-led dialogue about;

‣ Wars we don&apos;t want

‣  Disappeared Immigrants

‣  ICE Thugs

‣  Throes of a Dictator

‣  Voter Suppression 

‣  Upcoming Elections

‣  Constitutional Violations

‣  Rule-of-Law Violations

‣  Affordibility

‣  Escalating Prices

‣  Tariffs

‣  Epstein 

‣  Human Rights

‣  How to save our democracy...and so much more!

We have created THE CONVERSATION as an audience-led space for reflection and conversation about the daily US atrocities and the crumbling of our democracy and our Rule-Of-Law. 

We share our thoughts about the continuing chaos and destruction our country, while exploring ideas on how to move forward effectively.

This gathering is non-partisan and open to all. People of all backgrounds, beliefs, and political affiliations are welcome. The focus of THE CONVERSATION is humanitarian, moral, and grounded in shared human dignity.

There will be no featured speakers and no formal program. Instead, THE CONVERSATION centers the voices of those who attend. Community members are invited to speak from their seats (arranged in a circle to encourage talking to each other), sharing how they feel about the upending of our freedoms. 

This is a space to:

	•	Speak truth

	•	Use your voice

	•	Sit with one another in reflection and conversation 

What to Expect:

	•	Indoor, seated in a circle

	•	Quiet, respectful atmosphere

	•	Community sharing (voluntary)

	•	No microphones or amplification

	•	No chanting


What This Is / Is Not:

	✔ Conversation, ✖ not a protest

	✔ Non-partisan and community-centered

	✔ Open and welcoming to all

	✔ A space for shared humanity

	✖ Not a rally or boring meeting

All are welcome who come in the spirit of respect, reflection, and care for one another.

⸻

Good Trouble Indivisible is a Michigan nonprofit corporation

Action@goodtroubleindivisible.org

(616) 287-2221

⸻

This a local Indivisible event hosted by GOOD TROUBLE INDIVISIBLE; Saugatuck-Douglas Uniting West Michigan.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
