        <name>NO KINGS 3 Lansing Michigan Capitol</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS 3 Lansing Michigan Capitol</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Michigan State Capitol<br>100 N Capitol Ave<br>Lansing, MI 48933</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Michigan 7th District</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

On March 28th, rise up and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it. Join us at the State Capitol in Lansing to say: 


- Courage in Community

- No Kings

- ICE Out

- We the People

- VOTE


📍**Where:** Lansing Capitol, 100 N Capitol Ave, Lansing, MI

🗓️**Date:** Saturday, March 28


**Schedule of Events:**

🕔Time: **12PM - 4PM**

- **12PM -1:30 PM** Speakers
- **2PM** Sidewalk March
- **12PM - 4PM** Tabling

When our families are under attack and costs are pushing people to the brink, silence is not an option. We will defend ourselves and our communities against this administration’s unjust and cruel acts of violence. 

The President thinks his rule is absolute. In America, we don’t have kings, and we won’t back down against our neighbors being detained, chaos, corruption, and cruelty. We are proud of our free and fair elections and our Constitution and resist to save our freedoms and rebuild our future.

Learn about election protection, sign ballot petitions, engage in mutual aid, see effective community organizing in action. Find where you can best put your energy and skills toward the causes that matter the most to you. And gather energy for the work ahead.

**Bring items for donation at the event to drop off at MIResist tables:**

- Clothing, esp. new socks and underwear 

- Blankets 

- Towels 

- Personal care items and hygiene supplies. 


**Interested in volunteering for the event?** Please fill out this form: [No Kings 3 Volunteer Form](https://forms.gle/9yTnkuz68agWnTDc6)

**More money than time?** We are also taking monetary donations for this event: [Donate](https://secure.actblue.com/donate/nokingslansing)

Organized by the Courage in Community Coalition (Lansing No Kings Coalition)

_A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events._</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/893336/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
