        <name>BloomAIR Community Defense Training</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>BloomAIR Community Defense Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 29, 2026 at 6:45 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Monroe County Library - Ellettsville Branch<br>600 W Temperance St<br>Ellettsville, IN 47429</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible South Central Indiana</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Our friends from BloomAIR will conduct a 2-hour training covering three key topics:

1. Know your rights when interacting with law enforcement and federal agents

2. How to identify ICE

3. What to do if you see or hear about a potential ICE sighting. 

There will be time available for questions and answers as well. If you’re interested in organizing directly against ICE if they come to our community, or if you simply want to be prepared and empowered in the event of an ICE encounter, don’t miss this training.

Please arrive by 2:45pm so the training can begin promptly at 3:00pm.

### Photography and Video Policy
ISCI may take photos or videos at meetings and events to document, share, and promote our activities. When taking photos or videos, ISCI representatives will do their best to seek explicit consent before photographing individuals with their faces or names visible. We ask all participants taking personal photos or videos to seek consent as well and respect the wishes of those who do not want to be photographed or recorded. **Please note that in public settings, including protests, there is always the possibility of being identifiably photographed.** Ultimately, the responsibility for protecting our identity lies with each of us individually. If you are concerned about being photographed or recorded during Indivisible activities, we strongly encourage you to cover your face and other identifiable features.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/916007/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
