        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Mt. Airy, College Hill &amp; Northside Neighborhood Democrats March Monthly Meeting</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, March 26, 2026 at 10:30 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Just Q&apos;in BBQ<br>5903 Hamilton Ave<br>Cincinnati, OH 45224</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Hamilton County Dems (OH)</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>📅 Thursday, March 26
🕡 6:30 – 8:00 PM
📍 Just Q’in’
5903 Hamilton Avenue
College Hill

This month’s meeting will focus on Immigration.

We are honored to welcome Imam Ayman Soliman, the former chaplain at Cincinnati Children’s Hospital who was detained by ICE, as well as Ohio State Representative Cecil Thomas, who will discuss bills currently introduced in the Ohio Legislature concerning immigrants.

We will also hear from Meeka Owens and Stephanie Dumas, candidates for County Commissioner.

Join us for an important and timely conversation. All are welcome.</p>
