    <Placemark>
        <name>NO KINGS ST LOUIS (DOWNTOWN)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS ST LOUIS (DOWNTOWN)</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Aloe Plaza<br>1820 Market St<br>St. Louis, MO 63103</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>NO KINGS RALLY &amp; MARCH

📍 Where: Aloe Plaza, 1820 Market Street,, St. Louis, MO 63103
📅 When: March 28, 2026
⏰ 1:00–1:30 PM: Rally
⏰ 1:30 PM: No Kings March (begins and ends at Aloe Plaza)

NO KINGS is a peaceful national day of action. We are coming together to stand against authoritarianism, corruption, and the growing threat of fascism under the Trump administration.

Fascism doesn’t arrive all at once—it shows up as state violence, as armed ICE agents terrorizing immigrant communities, as detentions, disappearances, raids, and fear, and as violence directed at citizens who dare to resist. Fascism shows up as marginalized communities losing their rights, and ends with everyone losing their rights. What we are witnessing is an abuse of power meant to intimidate, silence, and divide us. We refuse.

The idea of No Kings is foundational to this country. It was born in resistance and carried by people who understood that no leader rules by divine right. On March 28, we gather in St. Louis to make it unmistakably clear: power belongs to the people—not to authoritarian strongmen, not to corrupt administrations, and not to militarized agencies acting with impunity.

This march is about taking a stand. We are coming together to oppose cruelty, corruption, and the use of violence as a way to govern. We are here to defend democracy, protect our communities, and support immigrants and everyone targeted by state repression.

The president may think his power is absolute, but in America, we do not have kings. We resist. We organize. We do not back down.

Commitment to Nonviolence
A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.&quot;

Legal Observers &amp; Safety
⚖️ Legal observers will be present to help protect participants’ rights.
🧠 Know your rights and look out for one another.
🟡 If you see someone being harassed, alert a safety or legal observer immediately.
📸 Document responsibly and safely. We take collective care seriously. Your safety and the safety of our most vulnerable neighbors matter to us.

How to Prepare
📢 Bring signs or props. Make your message impossible to ignore.
Ideas: “NO KINGS IN AMERICA,” “STOP ICE TERROR,” “FASCISM IS NOT FREEDOM,” “THE PEOPLE UNITED”
🌦️ Dress for the weather. We march rain or shine.
👥 Bring people with you. Let’s make this the biggest No Kings yet!
📸 Share the truth. Post photos and videos using #NoKingsSTL

Parking &amp; Transit
🅿️ Parking Garages:
Union Station
1515 Clark Ave
318 S 16th
East &amp; West Kiener iParkit Garages near the park
Street parking is available downtown
More info at https://www.stlouis-mo.gov/government/departments/treasurer/off-street-parking.cfm

🚇 Transit: (recommended)
MetroLink stops at Union Station
More info at metrostlouis.org/system-maps</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/901902/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
