        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stop the Cruelty, Westerville</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 27, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>675 Brooksedge Blvd<br>Westerville, OH 43081</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Central Ohio</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Stop the Cruelty: Westerville protest is at 675 Brooksedge Blvd. This is the Westerville ICE office. The nearest parking is at the Kroger strip mall on Schrock Rd.  We also have a group that goes down to the intersection of Schrock and Brooksedge and some of us are visiting 774 Park Meadow Rd., because ICE is renting an office for its legal team in that building. 

We provide the signs, which have red lettering on a white background and say, “Stop the Cruelty.”  We all use the same sign to maximize visual impact. We are a silent protest, although we do talk among ourselves. We have a policy of not hassling ICE officers who wander by. Anger and resentment are Donald Trump&apos;s tools, they&apos;re not ours. Everyone is welcome!</p>
