        <name>Cleveland May Day 2026: Workers Over Billionaires</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Cleveland May Day 2026: Workers Over Billionaires</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, May 1, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Cleveland Public Square<br>1 Public Square<br>Cleveland, OH 44114</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> May Day Strong</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Billionaires make and break every &apos;rule&apos;, it’s going to take more than a rally to stop them. 

**Our Demands for May 1st**
- No more war. Billions for war and genocide profiteers, while private prisons expand and schools close.
- Tax the rich so our families, not their fortunes and the war, come first.
- Abolish ICE. No private armies terrorizing our neighborhoods.

Labor is the source of all wealth, and entitled to all it creates. So we are showing our unity through a day of **No Work No School No Shopping.** 

We know that there are too many without the freedom to exercise these actions safely and securely yet, and that&apos;s why we organize from now until  we mark International Workers Day, May 1st, through action and community.

*Please note: A core principle behind all our events is a commitment to collective safety through nonviolent action. International Workers Day has historically been targeted, indeed May Day&apos;s roots lie in Haymarket Square. We encourage all participants to seek to de-escalate potential confrontation.*</p>
