        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Fridays With(out) Fetterman</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 6:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>City County Building<br>414 Grant St<br>Pittsburgh, PA 15219</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Pittsburgh</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>For the week of March 27 ONLY, the weekly protest will be on SATURDAY, MARCH 28 at noon at the City County building so we can join the NO KINGS RALLY!

There will be NO Friday protest on March 27.

Regular Friday protests return on APRIL 3 as we welcome PROGRESS PA as our event partner. 

Mondays With(out) McCormick is now Fridays With(out) Fetterman!

Indivisible Pittsburgh and Mondays With(out) McCormick are re-launching weekly protests outside of Senator Fetterman&apos;s office every Friday at noon. His job is to represent ALL of us. Instead he supports ICE&apos;s actions against our neighbors and buddies around with our other non-responsive senator, Dave McCormick. We need him to do better.

Join us each Friday at noon! Dress warmly, bring a friend and a sign if you have one.

If your organization would like to host a Fridays With(out) Fetterman, please reach out to us.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.</p>
