        <name>National F*ck ICE Protest</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>National F*ck ICE Protest</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 11, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Greene County Jail / Sex Offender Registration<br>1199 N Haseltine Rd<br>Springfield, MO 65802</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> 50501Missouri</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On April 11th at High Noon, people across the country will step outside, find the nearest place where ICE is unjustly caging human beings, and make their presence - and their contempt - impossible to ignore. 

This is not a single march in a single city. This is a simultaneous national action, coast to coast, at concentration camps, detention facilities, processing centers, and county jails where the machinery of this administration&apos;s cruelty operates every single day behind walls and fences and the calculated indifference of people who have decided that some human beings don&apos;t count. 

But they do count. We&apos;re counting them. And we&apos;re showing up. 

Join Southern Missouri Immigration Alliance (SMIA), 50501 Missouri, and The ReSisters at the Greene County Jail on Saturday, April 11th, at 12pm to demand change and accountability. 

SMIA will be accepting phone charger donations at the event. Phone chargers will be added to the care packages SMIA provides to people who are released from Greene County Jail.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/926996/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
