    <Placemark>
        <name>BLAI 287(g) Action Planning Meeting</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>BLAI 287(g) Action Planning Meeting</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 30, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>UCC<br>415 Juniper St<br>Brainerd, MN 56401</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Brainerd Lakes Area Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## Civic Engagement  Meeting

Crow Wing County’s partnerships with ICE in the form of both **287(g) Task Force &amp; Warrant Service Officer Program agreements**, as well as the **IGSA agreement** that enables the Crow Wing County jail to use beds to hold and detain individuals in ICE custody.

We believe we are most powerful when we organize together and coordinate efforts to apply strategic pressure on locally elected officials to reverse these agreements.

### Our goals for gathering in person:

- Share more information about the 287(g) and IGSA agreements  
- Discuss recent events, facts, and information relevant to our organizing efforts  
- Discuss our goals  
- Explore possible strategies (near-term and long-term) and gather your input  
- Share language for how to discuss our efforts in the community (including language and questions to support you as you may choose to engage with locally elected officials via email, private meetings, and/or public meetings)  
- Answer questions and activate the collective wisdom in the room  
- Determine next steps, communication norms, and action items  

We’re looking forward to seeing you.

In solidarity ✊🏿✊🏾✊🏽✊🏼✊🏻</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/893926/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
