Our march begins at 5 PM at the Old Ice Rink (the lawn at the corner of N Pine St. and E Cherry St. across from Burger King). We&apos;ll march a mile to Ratingen Platz (5 S Market St.), where our rally will begin around 5:45 PM. If you would like to skip the march, we suggest arriving at the Platz by 5:30 PM. Parking is available downtown near the Platz and on the USD campus in Lot 4 and Lot 24 near the Old Ice Rink (find them on the [campus parking map](https://www.usd.edu/-/media/Project/USD/DotEdu/About/Campus-Map-Directions-and-Parking/CampusParkingMap.pdf?rev=308620809791452f8a5f359b9705564f)). Public restrooms are available at the Muenster University Center (on the march route) and XIX Brewing Company (near the Platz).

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
