        <name>No Kings Rally After Party with Rep. April McClain Delaney</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>No Kings Rally After Party with Rep. April McClain Delaney</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 8:30 PM UTC - 10:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>118 E Church St<br>Frederick, MD 21701</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> April McClain Delaney for Congress</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>No Kings Rally After Party with Rep. April McClain Delaney

The rally doesn&apos;t stop when the speeches end. Join us for the No Kings Rally After Party with Congresswoman April McClain Delaney at the beautiful Gaslight Gallery in the heart of Downtown Frederick&apos;s Historic District.

Come celebrate, connect, and keep the energy going over refreshments and real conversation with your Congresswoman.

April will be speaking about her Keep ICE Out of Washington County Act, landmark legislation to block ICE&apos;s secretive plans for a 1,500-bed detention warehouse in Williamsport. She&apos;ll lay out her push for common-sense reforms: mandatory warrants, body cameras, and an end to the abuses she witnessed firsthand in Baltimore.

This is your chance to meet April face to face, share what&apos;s on your mind, and be part of the conversation about what&apos;s at stake for Frederick and Western Maryland  strengthening working families, protecting our communities, and defending democratic values against the forces that threaten them.

The Gaslight Gallery offers an intimate, welcoming setting for gatherings like this. Our event is free and please register. 

Light refreshments will be served.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/917249/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
