        <name>&quot;Coffee and Conversation: Unpacking ICE&quot; with the PA 10th District Network</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>&quot;Coffee and Conversation: Unpacking ICE&quot; with the PA 10th District Network</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 18, 2026 at 2:30 PM UTC - 4:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Simpson Library<br>16 N Walnut St<br>Mechanicsburg, PA 17055</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>As the landscape of immigration enforcement shifts rapidly in early 2026, staying informed is no longer optional—it is 100%  essential for community safety and advocacy. Join PA 10th District Network for a 90-minute Coffee &amp; Conversation to unpack ICE’s investigative and removal branches.  

We will dive into the reality of the 2026 enforcement climate, clarify the persistent legal gaps in due process, and provide actionable ” Know Your Rights” strategies. Whether you’re an advocate for or against current ICE practices, a community member, or simply looking to better understand these policies, come for the caffeine and stay for some clarity needed to navigate this complex era and be a part of this conversation.

Maximum for Group is 25 persons; please sign up soon! 

This is the first of a series of these events.    Light refreshments will be available. 

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
