        <name>Light the Way - Kensington</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Light the Way - Kensington</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 31, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Southeast side of Summit Ave and Knowles Avenue in Kensington, MD.<br>Summit Ave, Kensington, MD 20895<br>Kensington, MD 20895</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Be the change you want to see. Inspire others to stand up for justice.
We rally on the public sidewalk near the SE corner on Summit Avenue and Knowles Avenue. Near the skate park. Our gathering is child and dog friendly. 
Bring a neighbor! Bring a sign, or choose one of ours, to show your support for our immigrant neighbors and stand up against ICE and this lawless administration.
There is typically a line of traffic at this intersection at evening rush hour. Let&apos;s show them that Kensington cares about all of our neighbors! 

Sign Suggestions; Feed the Hungry, Shelter the Homeless, Embrace Diversity, Protect our Immigrant Neighbors.

This a local Indivisible event.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values. *</p>
