        <name>Calling All Resistance Knitters/Crocheters - Melt the Ice Hat Knit-In</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Calling All Resistance Knitters/Crocheters - Melt the Ice Hat Knit-In</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 29, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>The Shops at Kenilworth<br>800 Kenilworth Dr<br>Towson, MD 21204</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Allies for Democracy</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>In the 1940s, Norwegians quietly defied Nazi occupation by knitting and wearing red, pointed hats with tassels. A simple garment became an act of protest.

While Minnesota knitters revived this tradition during a recent surge there, we are now shifting our focus closer to home. With indications that ICE activity may increase in Maryland and other states, we are preparing to show up in solidarity here.

Join us as we knit and crochet *Melt the Ice Hats*. These red hats will be ready to offer warmth and visibility wherever they are needed next.

🧶 **Next Melt the Ice Hat Knit-In**  
📅 **When:** Sundays, February 15 - March 8, 2026
⏰ **Time:** 2–4 pm  
📍 **Where:** The Shops at Kenilworth Mall – Common Area  

**How:** Bring red yarn and needles or a hook if you have them. Knit and crochet patterns may be found on Ravelry. Beginners welcome, and supplies may be available to share.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/899993/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
