        <name>ICE Out of Home Depot/ICE Out for Good!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out of Home Depot/ICE Out for Good!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, April 12, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Red Rose Commons<br>1700 Fruitville Pike<br>Lancaster, PA 17601</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Lancaster Together</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Home Depot depends on the labor of immigrant workers, from construction to disaster recovery, profiting from global markets while turning its back on vulnerable communities here at home. This injustice cannot continue. Together, we have the power to demand accountability and justice.

Join us as we make it impossible for Home Depot to ignore the voices of the people. We stand united, sending a clear message that our communities deserve protection, respect, and solidarity—not neglect.

Here in Lancaster we have been hosting a series of sustained events to continue the pressure on the Home Depot corporation and the wider Lancaster County community. We gather along Fruitville Pike with our signs and our presence demonstrating our support for our immigrant neighbors. We encourage the Home Depot to publicly condemn the ICE raids taking place on or near their properties. We urge our community to condemn the cruel and illegal actions of ICE throughout this country. We come together to be an example for corporations and our local community to ACT, to SPEAK UP, and to take a STAND!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/917515/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
