        <name>April SURJ members General Meeting in the Eno River Area!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>April SURJ members General Meeting in the Eno River Area!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, April 12, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>1805 Chapel Hill Rd<br>Durham, NC 27707</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Showing Up for Racial Justice</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The right has revved up their attacks on our communities and neighbors, and now is the time fight back. 

We&apos;ll be continuing our work of **Block &amp; Build**: defending our communities from harm while building the power we need to win long-term change. We do this by focusing on two concrete areas: Strengthening and participating in [**Siembra’s organizing**](https://www.siembranc.org/) to resist government overreach and ICE raids while also moving people to action in [**SURJ’s national campaigns**](https://surj.org/current-campaigns/).


✨ **SAVE THE DATE** ✨
**Sunday, April 12th
1:00–3:00pm** (+ social time afterwards!)
Location will be downtown Durham. Make sure to **RSVP** so we can confirm the location with you!

**What we WILL be doing**: 
We’ll share updates on ongoing SURJ members’ work in the Eno River area and talk about specific projects to plug into. This includes some specific workstreams from our brainstorming in the last General Meeting, a proposal to organize MN Solidarity Parties or potlucks with our friends and neighbors, and ways to plug into ongoing work nationally and locally

**Who SHOULD attend**
Are you interested in building deeper, long-term relationships with other white people who want to fight for racial and economic justice by building power together in our community?

You don’t need prior training, organizing experience, or deep familiarity with the work. This meeting is for people who are ready to move toward action and shared responsibility—not just learning about the work. If that sounds like you, we’d love to have you.

*Introduction to SURJ: Showing Up for Racial Justice (SURJ) is a national organization that organizes white people to fight for racial and economic justice. For too long, the Right has used racism to divide us and protect the wealth and power of billionaires. Locally, we are SURJ volunteers in the Eno river area who work to turn concern into action by bringing people together to resist harm in our communities and build the skills, commitments, and collective power needed for lasting change.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/917572/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
