<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Engaged Defenders for Democracy</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Please join Engaged Defenders for Democracy as will gather to demonstrate at the ICE facility in Cary. We will stand along Evans Road at the corner of Evans and Centrewest Court, near the Cary ICE office (140 Centrewest Ct, Cary). 

Parking is available along Centrewest Court, or along Quade Drive (off Evans Road). This action serves to let ICE know we do not welcome them here and also make community residents aware that ICE has an office - and an ongoing presence - right here in Cary.

This will be a nonviolent demonstration. We are here to say ICE is not welcome. We are standing up for what we believe in. We want to inspire people to join us and grow our movement!

Please bring signs; no swastikas please.

We are excited to see you there and stand together for our country and let ICE know they are not welcome!

See you every Friday morning engaging drivers in Cary.

Please join our Substack: https://substack.com/profile/115484101-engaged-defenders-4-democracy

For more ED4D Mobilize Events: https://www.mobilize.us/engagedefendersfordemocracy/</p>
