        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS Middlesex Borough</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 7:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Ronald S. Dobies Municipal Building<br>1198 Mountain Ave<br>Middlesex, NJ 08846</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Middlesex Borough Democratic Organization</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.

This community gathering is in conjunction with Dunellen Borough Democrats.  

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it. Join us.


We will be gathering in front of the Municipal Building from 2pm - 3:30pm. Although there is no dedicated seating, you are welcome to bring your own chair to the event.



No Kings began in 2025 as a single day of defiance and has become a sustained national resistance to tyranny, spreading from small towns to city centers and across every community determined to defend democracy. Our peaceful movement is bigger than ever.

A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.

Bring signs that can be easily seen by passing cars. We recommend the following: The signs should be at least 2 feet on a side with big letters that are several inches high. The signs should have simple slogans that are easy to read. 

Possible sign slogans:
- No Kings! No Trump!
- No Crowns! No Kings! No Trump!
 - Dictators Fear Democracy
- Protect our Democracy!
-We the People, Believe in Democracy!
 - Disarm and Disband ICE! 
- No More Lies!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/918890/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
