        <name>Stronger than Fear: Know Your Rights Outreach in Paterson</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stronger than Fear: Know Your Rights Outreach in Paterson</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 11, 2026 at 2:30 PM UTC - 4:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Paterson<br>Market St. and Main St.<br>Paterson, NJ 07505</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> AAPI New Jersey</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Together, we are stronger than fear! Please join AAPI NJ and partners for visits to support immigrant-owned small businesses Paterson as they brace for escalated ICE activity. 

Speakers of Bengali, Arabic, or Spanish are especially needed to help us talk with business owners about what they&apos;ve been experiencing, their legal rights in encounters with ICE, and how they can protect their employees.

No language skills? No problem! You can still help with outreach in English using our translated materials and show support for these businesses by walking and shopping with us.

No cost to attend, but please bring funds to cover any purchases and RSVP for the meeting point. We&apos;ll start with a brief orientation. See you there!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/914903/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
