        <name>NO KINGS Cornwall NY</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS Cornwall NY</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 6:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Cornwall Main St Plaza Sidewalk<br>45 Quaker Ave<br>Cornwall, NY 12518</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

&quot;A nation that should be dedicated to freedom cannot tolerate this cruelty carried out in its name.

We will stand with our community members and fellow Americans who may be affected by the current brutal actions of ICE and the authoritarian policies of the Trump Administration.

America has progressed only when its people had the courage to challenge injustices and hold our nation accountable to its ideals. The strength of our nation has always rested on the rule of law, justice, and equal rights for all.

America was founded in ousting of a king, tyrants, and unchecked authority. Our strength as a nation has always rested on the rule of law, equal justice, and the courage of ordinary citizens to take a stand against unfair systems.



We protest to stand for the ideas and foundations that our beautiful nation was built upon. ICE’s brutality, sanctioned by the Trump Administration, is nothing more than a bunch of fear-mongers and hate-mongers abusing their sense of ‘power’ to terrorize, divide, and dehumanize.

It is our duty as Americans to protect the weak and speak up for those who cannot speak up for themselves. And for America to be truly united, we cannot reserve justice for the few. Every soul in this nation, foreign or domestic, deserves the chance to live their lives in peace and without fear.&quot; -Michael Duffy

In addition, I will be hosting another protest with Standing Up For Science on March 7th in the same location. STAND UP FOR EVIDENCE BASED POLICES.

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it. Join us.

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/901929/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
