    <Placemark>
        <name>NO KINGS Norman</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS Norman</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 8:30 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Legacy Park<br>1898 Legacy Park Dr<br>Norman, OK 73069</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

What began in 2025 as a single day of defiance has become a sustained national resistance to tyranny, spreading from small towns to city centers and across every community determined to defend democracy. Our peaceful movement is bigger than ever.

When our families are under attack and costs are pushing people to the brink, silence is not an option. We will defend ourselves and our communities against this administration’s unjust and cruel acts of violence.

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it. Join us.

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*

Location and Time

Our March rally will take place on Saturday, March 28, from 3:30 PM to 6:00 PM.

This rally will take place in two locations. 

At 3:30, we will begin our rally program at Legacy Park.
At 4:30, attendees can participate in a march to the bridge demonstration at Rock Creek Rd. and I-35. 
At 5:30, No Kings Norman will lead a march back to Legacy Park and the event will end at 6:00 PM. (Be sure to take any trash with you and dispose of it!)

Both locations will have volunteers from No Kings Norman available for the entirety of the event (3:30 PM - 6:00 PM). Attendees are welcome to be at either location for part/all of the event.


Speakers

Our speaker line-up is as follows:

Jeff Pixley will speak on first amendment and military members being silenced
Mitchell Jacob will speak on democracy
Helen Grant will speak on how the city is handling ICE and what we can do as citizens
Jinx Barber will speak on the dangers of christian nationalism.

We will also hear from representatives of a few of the tabling organizations.

Tabling Organizations

The organizations below will have tables at the event. We strongly encourage attendees to visit these tables and get involved with the work of these organizations.

Norman Indivisible
General Strike US
Women in Action for All
Cleveland County Votes
Red Dirt Collective
Be SMART
Cleveland County Young Democrats
Sierra Club of OK
OU AAUP (American Association of University Professors)
Norman DSA (Democratic Socialists of America)
West Wind Unitarian Universalist Congregation
GrooveFest

Our Commitment to Nonviolence

A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.

No Kings Norman will have a dedicated safety team and will be in contact with NPD as needed to prioritize the safety of all attendees. 

At Legacy Park, peacekeepers will be spread throughout the amphitheater, around the water feature and in the field to the north of the amphitheater. Some will walk around the entirety of the crowd during the event and some will be stationary. There will also be peacekeepers at the Rock Creek Rd bridge over I-35 (both the north and south sides) for the entirety of the event.

Parking and Transit

We anticipate a large crowd at No Kings Norman and there are a number of other events happening at the same time, so we recommend carpooling and using public transportation as possible.

There is free parking near both sites, but space is limited and you may have difficulty finding a spot. There is ample parking in the businesses surrounding Legacy Park. If you do use business parking, we encourage you to visit the business before or after the event.

Norman Embark (Bus) Service

Norman buses run from 10a-6p on Saturday. The 110 runs hourly from the Downtown Transit Center-Main Street-24th NW-Tecumseh/Healthplex and returns via the same route. 

Here is a link to the route information. This is a live link and has current arrival and departure times and is generally accurate: Route 110 (https://go.embarkok.com/routes/embark:rt-110/stops/embark:rt-110:1:01).

The closest stop to our Rally Location is 24th and Legacy Park.
The closest stop to Rock Creek Road is Conference Drive.

You can also use the Embark Connect App (https://www.embarkok.com/mobile-apps) to track bus info as well.

Weather Awareness

We are hopeful for a partly-cloudy day with a high of 69 and a low of 49. However, we always encourage all attendees to prepare to raise your voice responsibly!

Please be sure to keep an eye on any signs or loose items to prevent wind-related issues.
Make hydration a priority: we will be keeping stations stocked and accessible, but please be responsible and bring some water with you.
Please consider bringing a hat and using sun protection (sunscreen, etc.).
Please consider bringing a light rain jacket or poncho, in case a brief shower develops.
Remember, this is Oklahoma, so be weather aware: monitor conditions and check in if winds increase unexpectedly. We will be doing the same.

Frequently Asked Questions

March

There will be a march as part of our rally, beginning at Legacy Park at 4:30. The march will be just under a mile each way, so be prepared to walk for 2 miles round trip with a 30 minute break at the bridge. For attendees who do not wish to march, or who are otherwise unable to march, there will be continued rally programming at Legacy Park until 6:00 PM.

All participants are advised to utilize sidewalks and easements as well as follow all crosswalk and traffic lights. Volunteer marshals will be assisting in keeping the flow of the procession safe throughout the march.
Due to possible safety concerns, we will not be publicly sharing our march route.

Organizations

Tables/tents of partnering organizations will be located along the north portion of the paved path that encircles the water feature.

Bathrooms

There are publicly-accessible restrooms at Legacy Park, located on the North end of the park (to the right of the stage from general seating, past the organization tables).

There are no public restrooms easily accessible at the Bridge Demonstration.

Medics

We will have designated volunteer medics, located both at a medic table at Legacy Park and roaming during the rally and demonstration. There will be at least one medic at each location from 3:30 PM - 6:00 PM.

The medic table at Legacy Park will be located by the north arch in the paved area between the amphitheater and Legacy Park Dr.

You can contact any No Kings Norman volunteer to be connected with a medic, or shout “Medic!”

Getting Involved

If you would like to be involved as a volunteer for No Kings Norman, please send an email to indivisiblenormanok@gmail.com.

Please help make No Kings Norman even bigger and better by making a donation (https://secure.actblue.com/donate/indivisiblenorman?fbclid=IwY2xjawPpBy1leHRuA2FlbQIxMABicmlkETFFUHFnSzhWWGZIdWpoMVNBc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MgABHl9RgU8cH2_Vtu7wrWgmZfq9Fz-zhPsAaSnPhRH1AuNtrHY7qpo4Lu-CeXEG_aem_UI3beIPKh_tGeLI0DCiaOg). Donations help us to pay for permits, printing, medical and safety supplies, and other direct costs. 

Not Sure What To Say…?

Feel free to start one of our favorite chants as we march!

No justice! No peace!
&apos;Til Trump is impeached!

No Trump! No KKK! No fascist USA!

¡La migra, la policía, la misma porquería!

Power to the people
No one is illegal!

No borders! No nations!
Stop the deportations!

From Palestine to Mexico
All the walls have got to go!

Cops and borders, we don’t need ’em
What we want is total freedom!

We don’t want a prison nation
Stop mass incarceration!

Say it once, say it twice,
we will not put up with ICE!

(To the rhythm of “Macho Man”)
Taco Taco Man,
We gotta impeach the Taco Man 

(To the rhythm of “HOT TO GO”)
G-O-T-T-O-G-O
Trump &amp; ICE have got to go!

Pre-No Kings Demonstration

There will be a multi-state bridge visibility demonstration along I-35 from Minnesota to Texas on Thursday, March 26, 2026 as a way to build momentum towards No Kings on Saturday, March 28, 2026. If you would like to participate in the one happening in Norman, please visit the Norman event page (https://dmbr.org/i-35-events/message-on-the-rock-creek-bridge-norman-ok) for more details.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/900723/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
