        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS JERSEY CITY</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 6:30 PM UTC - 8:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Berry Lane Park<br>1000 Garfield Ave<br>Jersey City, NJ 07304</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>From the first No Kings protests on June 14, 2025 to the general strike in Minneapolis, to the growing protests against Trump&apos;s illegal war on Iran, Resistance 2.0 against Trump and MAGA continues to grow. Our peaceful movement is bigger than ever. Join the next national day of action and help build the resistance in Jersey City.

When immigrant families and civil rights are under attack, when rising costs are pushing working people to the brink, and when fascist-minded billionaires unleash mass violence on the world, silence is not an option. We will defend ourselves and our communities against this administration’s attempts to divide our people and roll back democracy.

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. No war, no ICE, no racism, and no facism.

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
