        <name>Anniversary Protest the Cuts Rally</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Anniversary Protest the Cuts Rally</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, April 29, 2026 at 8:30 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>1715 NJ-35<br>Middletown Township, NJ 07748</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This is our Anniversary Rally!! On this date, we will celebrate our persistence and stamina because we have reached a milestone on this date -- we have protested weekly for an ENTIRE YEAR!!! With the exception of Christmas Eve and New Year&apos;s Eve, we have protested every Wednesday now for 52 weeks! We invite all activists who want to protest against Trump, Rep. Chris Smith&apos;s lack of backbone, federal government overreach, the illegal war in Iran, the cuts to Medicaid, the cuts to SNAP, the cuts to the VA, ICE abuse, the lack of due process for immigrants, and the dissolution of USAID. We also invite reporters to attend this rally to meet our amazing team of activists and to learn about what keeps us motivated to keep showing up week after week. 

Join Indivisible, Middletown Outrage into Action and Shore Area NOW as we protest in Middletown!! We show up to voice a slew of concerns, including ICE’s illegal detention of immigrants without due process, ICE’s escalation of violence in Minneapolis, the cuts to Medicaid, USAID, SNAP, and other essential federal programs, the tax cuts to billionaires, the illegal invasion of both Iran and Venezuela, and Trump’s threats to other countries as well. Until Rep. Chris Smith and the rest of Congress begin to show genuine congressional oversight and push back against the unconstitutional actions of the Trump administration, we will protest.

Join us Wednesday from 4:30 to sunset in front of Rep. Chris Smith&apos;s Middletown office located at 1715 Route 35! While Chris Smith has abandoned this office, we have not. His office building is just north of the Middletown Post Office on 35. Look for us roadside on the grass in front of the office building&apos;s parking lot. Please do NOT park at the post office or at the 1715 office building. We park at the Staples/Mattress store parking lot and walk over. Remember to bring your signs, your flags, and your friends!! Thank you!!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values. *

