        <name>FLOCK CAMERAS: What are they and Why should you be concerned?</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>FLOCK CAMERAS: What are they and Why should you be concerned?</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, April 2, 2026 at 10:30 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Saratoga Springs Public Library - Dutcher Community Room<br>49 Henry St<br>Saratoga Springs, NY 12866</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible ADK/Saratoga</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>There&apos;s been a lot of buzz lately about **Flock cameras**, and we&apos;ve got a bunch right here in Saratoga! Come learn all about Flock cameras, presented by our friends at Indivisible Albany.

This will be a discussion about the widespread proliferation of Flock camera systems, including throughout the Capital District, as we launch our public education campaign about how Flocks work, where they are, how the data is retained and, more importantly, how this data is being funneled to federal agencies such as ICE to target and track immigrant communities. 

We will also discuss actions that you can take to fight back against the installation of Flock cameras and to demand accountability for those already in use. We think this will be an extremely informative session and we hope you can join us.

*Indivisible ADK/Saratoga is a local chapter of [Indivisible](http://Indivisible.org), active in NY&apos;s Saratoga, Warren, and Washington counties, that welcomes people with our shared values and goals. We organize and mobilize for actions that safeguard and advocate for vulnerable communities, protect human rights, guard our planet, elect progressive candidates, and protect democracy.*

Find us online:

[Website](https://www.indivisibleadksaratoga.com)

[Bluesky](https://bsky.app/profile/indivisible-adk.bsky.social)

[Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/share/g/19myt9wGmE)

[Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/indivisibleadksaratoga/)

Email us: indivisibleadksaratoga@gmail.com</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/926565/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
