        <name>SATS @2: SIGNS OF SOLIDARITY in SO. BRONX - Help workers Know their Rights w/ Target Majority NYC</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>SATS @2: SIGNS OF SOLIDARITY in SO. BRONX - Help workers Know their Rights w/ Target Majority NYC</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 25, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Columbus Cir<br>New York, NY 10023</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Swing Left</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Keep showing up in solidarity with our neighbors. These days of business outreach will work in either western midtown or the south Bronx. Everywhere we&apos;ve gone, we&apos;ve had really good experiences helping store managers, bar/restaurants, parking lots, etc to prepare and better protect employees in the event of ICE raids.

Join volunteers with Target Majority NYC to talk to business owners and managers and teach them the crucial Know Your Rights info they need to better protect their employees in the event of an ICE Raid. You&apos;ll help them put up signs to declare their solidarity, and to create as much protection as possible within their place of work.

We will provide training on the spot, but you can also start prepping now by visiting https://tinyurl.com/startSOS

**A core principle behind all Target Majority NYC events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values. We recommend all participants review [Indivisible&apos;s safety and security resources](https://indivisi.org/safety) before this event**</p>
