        <name>Weekly Vigil for Democracy at the Brooklyn Metropolitan Detention Center</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Weekly Vigil for Democracy at the Brooklyn Metropolitan Detention Center</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 31, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>116 29th St<br>Brooklyn, NY 11232</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Brooklyn</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us in standing up for our neighbors, held at the notorious prison in our own back yard. For years, the Metropolitan Detention Center has had a reputation for inhumane conditions: rancid food, lack of heating in winter and oppressive heat in summer. In 2020, an inmate named Jamel Floyd was killed by corrections officers by excessive use of force. Now, ICE is using the Metropolitan Detention Center to house our immigrant neighbors -- mothers, fathers, sons and daughters -- who have been taken from their homes, schools, and workplaces and held in detention.

Our fellow organizers at Good Shepherd Lutheran Church in Bay Ridge are holding for a weekly vigil outside the MDC to call for the release of ICE detainees, and to stand against the inhumane treatment of our neighbors. Supporters are invited to bring signs, to sing or play music, and to solemnly bear witness in solidarity. Together we will build and strengthen the vital community connections.

* We gather first at the corner of 3rd Avenue and 29th Street.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/818180/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
