            <Data name="LocationType"><value>exact</value></Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
            <coordinates>-74.0027448,40.6594299,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
        <name>Weekly Vigil for Democracy at Brooklyn’s ICE Jail</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Weekly Vigil for Democracy at Brooklyn’s ICE Jail</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, April 7, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>116 29th St<br>Brooklyn, NY 11232</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Hands Off NYC</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Every Tuesday from 6-7pm, join Indivisible Brooklyn and our fellow organizers at Good Shepherd Lutheran Church in Bay Ridge for our weekly vigil outside the Metropolitan Detention Center (Third Ave. &amp; 29th St.), where 200 of our abducted neighbors have been imprisoned. Let’s stand firm against the inhumane treatment of our neighbors, and call for the release of all ICE detainees. Sing songs of resistance and bring signs to bear witness in solidarity.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/924827/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
