    <Placemark>
        <name>NO KINGS: Danbury March!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS: Danbury March!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>1 Ives St<br>Danbury, CT 06810</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

With tens of thousands of first generation immigrants, Danbury is the heart  of the immigrant community in Western Connecticut. It is no coincidence that Danbury  has become ground zero for the authoritarian regime in our area. ICE has repeatedly targeted our neighbors, tearing apart families who contribute to the fabric of the community. Meanwhile, federal budget cuts and chronic state underfunding are devastating  essential services that working-class residents depend on for survival. Public schools are underfunded. Food banks are depleted. 
The attacks on Danbury are not by chance, but because they represent the America that authoritarians and billionaires  fear most - diverse, united, and unwilling to bow. We are marching to show that we will not allow our neighbors in Danbury to be terrorized. We are stronger when we are united together. 
No kings. No silence. Just people power. ✊🏽

Join us in the streets for the Danbury March. Where our voices, our stories, and our communities come together to demand dignity, justice, and protection for all.

🗓 Saturday, March 28
📍 Danbury City Center Green
⏰ 3 PM Gather 4PM March 

Bring your signs, your instruments, your noise and show up strong.

We’re marching to:
• Defend our democracy
• Stand against ICE raids &amp; family separation
• Protect working families
• Reject policies that harm our communities
• Build solidarity across Western CT

And after? We keep showing up. Join us for Dining for Justice supporting immigrant-owned restaurants and standing with our neighbors. ❤️

🔗 Sign up &amp; RSVP —


Dining for Justice: 
https://mobilize.us/s/fveXyB
#NoKings #WeThePeople #DanburyMarch #PeoplePower #ImmigrantJustice

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/905608/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
