    <Placemark>
        <name>NO KINGS Bismarck</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS Bismarck</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>ND State Capitol<br>600 E Boulevard Ave<br>Bismarck, ND 58501</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On March 28, we return to the streets for the third round of No Kings—a nationwide mobilization to declare that in the United States, power belongs to the people, not to a single individual or billionaires.  
This movement is a direct response to the administration’s escalating reign of terror, catalyzed by the tragic killings of Renée Good and Alex Pretti in Minneapolis by federal agents. We are standing together to demand an immediate end to militarized ICE raids, the removal of masked federal forces from our communities, and a total overhaul of our immigration system to ensure human rights and due process for all.  
Defending Democracy &amp; Civil Rights: Protect our right to vote and our freedom of speech against executive overreach.
Transparency &amp; Accountability: Demand the full, unredacted release of the Epstein files to provide justice for survivors and ensure the DOJ is not used as a tool for political retribution. 
Economic Justice: End the policies that drive up the cost of living for families while enriching billionaire allies.
Our NO KINGS protest will be holding a fundraising effort and in-kind donations drive for Bismarck Global Neighbors, a nonprofit organization that supports new Americans coming to North Dakota for work and safety. 
BGN is facing a significant loss in federal funding, but the number of New Americans relocating here continues to grow. Supporting  this organization can help ensure they have the resources to provide a stable foundation and a warm welcome for our newest neighbors during this critical time.
To donate online: https://givebutter.com/gn_donations  
Checks can be made payable to Bismarck Global Neighbors and sent to 206 E Broadway Ave, Bismarck, ND 58501
In addition to monetary donations, the following items can be brought to the NO KINGS protest and dropped off in the white bins that will be set up on the south end of the Capitol grounds at 6th &amp; Boulevard.  
Toilet Paper
Paper Towels
Hand soap (bulk or individual)
Diapers Size 1-5
*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*

