    <Placemark>
        <name>How to Defend &amp; Support Neighbors Targeted by ICE Raids</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>How to Defend &amp; Support Neighbors Targeted by ICE Raids</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 31, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Dorchester County Democrats</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Are you concerned about the people in our community who are being targeted by ICE raids?  Do you wish you could help but don&apos;t know what to do?

The Charleston Immigrant Community Hotline has the answers.

During this 90-minute webinar you will learn how you can participate in this all-volunteer effort to defend and support immigrants by systematically identifying, verifying, and reporting ICE activity within Berkeley, Charleston, and Dorchester counties.</p>
