        <name>Stand Up Against ICE at White Cap Business Park, Williston</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stand Up Against ICE at White Cap Business Park, Williston</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 25, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>White Cap Business Park<br>426 Industrial Ave<br>Williston, VT 05495</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Champlain Valley Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join a small group that is standing up against ICE on Wednesday afternoons at the White Cap Business Park in Williston. This is the location of a new ICE facility where contractors will review social media posts of  &quot;persons of interest&quot;, and also spy on their friends, family, neighbors and co-workers.   Demonstrate your opposition to ICE&apos;s brutal tactics, their refusal to identify themselves or wear body cams,  and their total disregard for due process. 

Bring a sign or an American flag.

This event is hosted by Champlain Valley Indivisible. We&apos;ll be standing in the public right-of-way along Industrial Ave; our right to peaceful assembly is protected by the First Amendment. 

Please register so we know to expect you, and can reach out if we need to cancel for weather or other concern.  

Important:
--there is no sidewalk on the right-of-way, so be prepared to stand in snow.  If we&apos;ve had a recent snow, it might be smart to bring a shovel. 
--DO NOT PARK in White Caps. There is public parking along the street on Avenue C, and at Rossingol Park   (a 3 minute walk).
--if you have time, make a sign that refers specifically to ICE. 

A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.</p>
