        <name>HCC &amp; Community Walk-Out / Walk-In / Speak-Out re ICE</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>HCC &amp; Community Walk-Out / Walk-In / Speak-Out re ICE</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 25, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 4:15 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>303 Homestead Ave<br>Holyoke, MA 01040</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Northampton-Swing Left Western MA</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This event was posted by Indivisible Northampton on behalf of #HolyokeSanctuary.

We&apos;re inviting all community members who are able to come and show their support by joining the HCC students in a protest against ICE&apos;s actions in our country AND to demand that HCC immediately complies with the governor&apos;s executive order no. 650. Currently, our school does not have any available information, messaging, planned trainings, etc., regarding what staff and students can do to protect themselves, nor have they specified what measures HCC will take should ICE agents arrive on our campus.

This is a family friendly peaceful protest that will feature amplified sound systems, music, chants, stories being spoken, our demands being read, and a petition to sign to demand that HCC complies immediately. 

We are wearing black shirts, nondescript clothes (no branding, specific flags, etc.) and people are welcome to bring signage that shares a message of solidarity with the protest&apos;s focus.

This is a joint effort between HCC student clubs, faculty, and interested community members, and posted on the group&apos;s behalf by Indivisible Northampton.</p>
