        <name>Stop – This Is a Tax Robbery! Standout</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stop – This Is a Tax Robbery! Standout</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 11, 2026 at 2:30 PM UTC - 3:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Bacon Street &amp; East Main Street<br>Westminster, MA 01473</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> MassDems</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This peaceful standout is a response to a billionaire class that is extracting everything from working people and giving nothing back. Your taxes fund yachts, the ICE and CBP slush fund, unconstitutional government surveillance, and war crimes disguised as military operations nobody voted for, while SNAP gets cut, health insurance and prescriptions get more unaffordable, and working families choose between rent, healthcare, childcare, and groceries. We&apos;re not demanding charity. We&apos;re demanding much fairer tax policy that builds America up, not break it down. The village built everything. It&apos;s time the castle paid its share. Join us to say, “Stop – This is a tax robbery!”

- Bring your signs 
- Bring your power
- Bring your people

This is a safe environment for all of our communities: Teachers, Veterans, Retirees. Moms, Dads, brothers, sisters, teens and children (our next generation of activists!). People of all colors, race, genders, ethnicities, abilities, and disabilities. LGBTQIA+ … you name it YOU ARE WELCOME!

Sign ideas: 
My Taxes Should Not Fund War Crimes
- No Taxes for Dictators / Fascists
- Tea&apos;s Up in 2026 Like It&apos;s 1776
- Abolish ICE and Its Slush Fund
- Grifters aren’t patriots 
- Clean up on aisle 47

EXPECTATIONS: This will be a PEACEFUL standout. Violence of any kind will not be tolerated. Do not engage with any counter-protesters. Do not bring weapons of any kind, even if you have a license to carry.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/925268/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
