        <name>VAN Training</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>VAN Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 25, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Foxtail Coffee &amp; Kelly&apos;s Homemade Ice Cream - Wildlight<br>75980 William Burgess Blvd 4<br>Yulee, FL 32097</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Nassau County Democratic Party</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Unlock the Power of VAN: Training &amp; Access for Stronger Organizing


If we’re serious about winning elections and building power in our neighborhoods, we have to use the tools available to us effectively. One of the most important tools we have is the VAN database.



VAN (Voter Activation Network) is the system Democrats use to organize, track voter outreach, and make sure we’re reaching the right people at the right time. It allows us to:



Identify Democratic voters in our precincts
Track voter contact and engagement
Organize door-to-door canvasses
Run phone banks and text banks
Follow up with voters who need reminders or assistance
Monitor turnout and voting history


When used well, VAN turns good intentions into real results.



Why It Matters
Winning doesn’t happen by accident. It happens because volunteers know who to talk to, when to follow up, and how to make sure supporters actually show up to vote.



With proper VAN access and training, your team can:



Make sure voters in your neighborhood are registered and ready
Help identify new volunteers
Build stronger precinct-level organization
Follow up with infrequent voters who just need a nudge
Stay organized instead of guessing


It’s not just about Election Day. It’s about year-round engagement.



Upcoming VAN Training
📅 March 25th at 4:00 PM

📍 Yulee, FL



Advanced registration is required. Please sign up via Mobilize to reserve your spot. Space limited and there are a limited amount of registrants so please sign up early to claim your spot. 



This training will cover:

Basic navigation and searching
Pulling walk and call lists
Data entry and best practices
Using VAN responsibly and securely
Turning data into action


Whether you’re brand new or just need a refresher, this session will help you feel confident and effective.



Ready to Level Up?
If you want to:

Strengthen your precinct
Grow volunteer capacity
Make sure your neighborhood is vote-ready
Or better understand how organizing works behind the scenes


Now is the time to get trained.

Elections are won by organized teams. VAN helps us organize smarter — and win stronger.


We hope to see you on March 25th. Sign up here to reserve your spot.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/905942/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
