        <name>Ride for Our Republic</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Ride for Our Republic</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 25, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:15 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Galaxy Park Kendall Sq<br>220-238 Main St<br>Cambridge, MA 02142</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This Wednesday March 25th we ride again to get the word out about NO KINGS 3 rally, sure to be the largest protest in US history, Saturday March 28th! 

We will gather in Galaxy Park at the intersection of Main St, 3rd St, and Broadway in Kendall Square at 5pm. From there we will ride on the streets from Cambridge, Somerville, and Arlington. 

Everyone have at least one large sign with &quot;No Kings 3 SAT&quot; attached to your bike or person! &quot;No War&quot; and &quot;No ICE&quot; signs would be great too!  

No Kings 3 Boston: https://www.mobilize.us/indivisible-ma/event/901135/

------------------------------------------------------

Ride for Our Republic is a recurring pro-democracy bike ride held on the last Saturday of each month that was held April-October 2025. In the spirit of Paul Revere and on the 250th anniversary of the first American Revolution, we ride to sound the alarm of tyranny and fight for our democracy.

Fascism cannot flourish where joy and solidarity thrive. That truth is the heartbeat of Ride for Our Republic: a growing community of cyclists reclaiming Boston’s streets and bike paths as spaces of protest, hope, and joyful resistance. 

Please follow our facebook page: www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100088170471304

Our monthly #Ride4Republic bike protests will restart in April 2026.
We’ll ride a 12.7-mile route (bike paths + roads), but you’re welcome to join or leave at the waypoints where we rally and connect.

Route:
Boston → Davis Sq (3.9 mi)
Davis Sq → Arlington Center (3.8 mi)
Arlington Center → Lexington Center (5 mi)

10:00am – Meet at Paul Revere Park near the playground (North Washington St., Charlestown) – rain or shine

10:45–11:00am – 7 Hills Park, Davis Square, Somerville behind the T station

11:30–11:45am – Uncle Sam Statue, Arlington Center

Ending Point – Lexington Center, Minuteman Bikeway 

Bring: bright colors or neon, pro-democracy costumes or signs (bike frame, basket, shirt, or bag), American flags, and No Kings signs. 

Don’t forget water, snacks, packed lunch, sunscreen, bike lock, and other ride supplies.

Yours in Solidarity and Joyful Resistance,

Ride for Our Republic

---------------

And if you see ICE, CALL LUCE HOTLINE: 617-370-5023 and keep our neighbors safe!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/785586/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
