        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>HANDS OFF BEVERLY</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Odell Veterans Memorial Park<br>56-98 Broadway<br>Beverly, MA 01915</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

HANDS OFF BEVERLY has had weekly protests since February 17, 2025. At that time we started with about 20 people. Since the murder of Renee Good we have grown to about 300-400 people every Saturday even in sub zero temperatures, snow and ice. We hosted the HANDS OFF protest on April 5, 2025 and drew about 300 people. At the first NO KINGS we had 700 people and at NO KINGS 2.0 over 1,500 joined us. People have had enough and are waking up to the sad reality that their action is required if they do not want to live in a dictatorship like Russia for the rest of their lives. We expect between 2,000 and 3,000 people for the NO KINGS 3.0 in Beverly. Well above the 3.5% goal. Our specialty is great music (DJ Jim), bubbles, cowbells, American Flags and a huge selection of signs to borrow. Join us for a great time. Visit us on line at handsoffbeverly.com. 

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
