        <name>Signs of Solidarity Business KYR Training Near N Lamar and W 29th Ave. April 12th</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Signs of Solidarity Business KYR Training Near N Lamar and W 29th Ave. April 12th</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, April 12, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>West 29th Avenue &amp; North Lamar Street<br>Wheat Ridge, CO 80214</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Denver Action</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Signs of Solidarity Training–April 12, NW Denver

ICE activity may not be in the news, but recent reports indicate that 15-20 people a day are being detained in Colorado and Wyoming.  Signs of Solidarity program volunteers visit small businesses to provide them with practical information about how to prepare for and respond to an ICE raid.  In addition to providing businesses with the information they need, Signs of Solidarity helps build community cohesion and resistance to ICE.

Join us on Saturday April 12 from 2:00-4:00 PM for training to become a Signs of Solidarity canvasser. 

Following the training, there will be opportunity to canvass with partners in the nearby community.

The Signs of Solidarity Program is sponsored by Indivisible Denver and the Denver Immigrant Partnership Team.  

Canvassing is a demonstration of our solidarity with all of our Denver community and has been received warmly by the businesses visited.  

Since our founding in 2016, Indivisible has been rooted in the belief that organized people can beat organized hate—and that our power comes not just from our numbers, but from how we show up. We reject all forms of political violence and intimidation, no matter the source or the target.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/926934/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
