        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Bannering on E Park St bridge over Hwy 183A in Cedar Park, Mondays, 3-5 pm</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 30, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>East Park Street &amp; 183A Shared Use Path<br>Cedar Park, TX 78613</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible 1431</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Indivisible 1431 and banner every Monday in January!

Help show Cedar Park how many of us work to end GOP fascism and corruption -- ICE OUT! No War! No Kings &amp; No Dictators, End GOP Corruption, Fund the ACA, and more.

Bring handheld signs for the bridge traffic. Our collection of banners overlooking the highway is growing fast!

Join us 3-5 pm for our peaceful banner and popup event, each January Monday afternoon.

While the large banners overlook the 183A tollway, several of us will proudly display signs facing traffic on E Park. 

Parking is easy, the bridge is &quot;protestor friendly.&quot; Only drawback is that no public rest room is available, so be prepared for that!

Hope to see you Monday!</p>
