    <Placemark>
        <name>ICE Watch - Bastrop, Tx (IWBT)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Watch - Bastrop, Tx (IWBT)</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 6, 2026 at 6:00 AM UTC - 6:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Across the country, the tide is turning as entire communities are stepping up and working together to say ICE Out. This will only continue if we organize — together. 

We are calling on communities to form ICE Out groups/committees in your neighborhood, or within your existing organizations, and organize collectively to protect our communities.

These groups/committees can work together to: 

* Push for proactive policies that decouple local law enforcement from ICE, such as getting ICE out of jails and ending collaboration with local police and fighting surveillance tools like Flock cameras.

* Push for policies that create barriers between ICE and sensitive locations such as churches, schools and daycare centers;

* ICE Out Committees can also be formed as line of defense, organizing:

     * Safety patrols in your neighborhood or at sensitive locations

     * Constitutional observers

     * Food delivery to affected immigrant community post-raids. 

     * Any other type of mutual aid or direct support for community 
members who fear ICE. This work spreads love, strengthens community, and resists the harm and destruction that ICE brings to our neighborhoods. 

If you are not at risk of deportation, we ask you to take action now. Be present. Be consistent. Build relationships. Show up as allies, witnesses, neighbors, and friends. Stand with immigrant workers peacefully with love and care.

Remember: Solo el pueblo salva al pueblo. Only the people save the people.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/917058/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
