    <Placemark>
        <name>UCF Strike for Change</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>UCF Strike for Change</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, April 10, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Memory Mall<br><br>Orlando, FL 32816</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Sunrise Movement</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On April 10, thousands of students at UCF are not going to class, not spending money, and standing up for what&apos;s right. Our demands are simple, and we DEMAND that the university administration listen to us. We have a right to a safe campus without fear of getting detained by ICE disguised as UCFPD, we have a right to quality professors with livable wages, and we have a right to know where our tuition money is going. 

We have planned for over a year with a vision of community at UCF. We want every RSO to table, every student to hang out, and everyone with skills in crafting, mending, and cooking to share their craft. We are building a movement of people who support each other and don&apos;t need to rely on big corporations. Organizers and community members from all over the city are joining us to show our strength. 

Will you make history with us?

Our Demands: 
1. End 287(g) and make UCF a sanctuary campus 
2. Grant the raise the faculty union asks for annually
3. Be transparent with the budget and endowment allocation</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/918697/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
