    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
        <name>Community Town Hall</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Community Town Hall</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, April 16, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 1:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Salida High School<br>26 Jones Ave<br>Salida, CO 81201</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Ark Valley Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>What happens in Chaffee County when ICE agents are present?

ICE activity has increased across Colorado, including in rural areas. Our community has also been touched, and many residents have expressed concern about the impact on families and neighbors. Questions are circulating: Will we see more ICE agents locally? How are our institutions prepared? What plans are in place? How do local law enforcement agencies interact with ICE?

Join the Chaffee Immigrant Partnership Team and Ark Valley Indivisible in this town hall to hear directly from local leaders about how our community responds, how agencies coordinate, and what residents can expect when immigration enforcement occurs locally.  Panelists include:

Chaffee County Sheriff Andy Rohrich
Salida Police Chief Russ Johnson
Salida School Superintendent David Blackburn
Mayor Justin Critelli
Chaffee County Commissioner P.T. Wood

They will address:

Current policies and procedures
How the Sheriff’s Office and Police Department interact with and respond to ICE
When and how local agencies coordinate or communicate with federal immigration authorities
The policies and responsibilities of the school district
How local agencies coordinate with each other
How information would be communicated to the public
What residents should do if they suspect ICE activity

Clear information helps reduce uncertainty. This town hall gives residents an opportunity to hear directly from local leaders and ask questions about how our community responds to ICE actions.

The event will include a moderated Q&amp;A session with attendees. 
Community members are invited to submit questions in advance by submitting when registering on Mobilize. 

Date:  Wednesday, April 15, 2026
Time:  6:00 – 7:30 PM (doors open at 5:30)
Location:  Salida High School Gym

&quot;The Salida School District does not approve nor disapprove the content of outside use as qualified under district policies.”</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/918613/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#exact</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
            <Data name="EventID"><value>918613</value></Data>
