        </Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
        <name>NO KINGS in Dripping Springs</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS in Dripping Springs</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 2:00 PM UTC - 4:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Veterans Memorial Park<br>511 E Mercer St<br>Dripping Springs, TX 78620</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>As we do at 9 am every Saturday morning, we will gather in downtown Dripping Springs, Texas to show our love for America, our love for our democratic traditions and our opposition to Trump&apos;s widening war on our rights and freedoms, and our nation&apos;s standing among the nations of the world.

We ask that you fly only American flags, using your signs to express your personal concerns with what is going on in our country right now:  ICE abuses, The War Against Iran, etc.  Wear costumes, do street theater, bring musical instruments, we will have fun, while letting Trump know we are not on board with his brand of governance.

So, join us at 9 am on March 28 to show our community What Democracy Looks Like, fly our American flags, display our signs, wave to passersby and meet your fellow Americans who do not like what Trump and his cronies are doing to our country.

We will meet afterwards at the Dripping Springs Distillery, just west of downtown, at 5330 Bell Springs Rd, Dripping Springs, TX 78620.  The bar, which also serves food, opens at 11:30 am.  It is a big place, and should accomodate our crowd, and provide us with a place to relax together after the protest.

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it. Join us.

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/916113/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
