        <name>NO KINGS Temple Terrace</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS Temple Terrace</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 2:00 PM UTC - 4:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Intersection in front of former Boston Market<br>East Fowler Avenue and North 56th Street<br>Temple Terrace, FL 33617</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Hillsborough County DEC</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## NO KINGS in the LAND OF THE FREE

#### Temple Terrace Democrats are joining up with the North Tampa Democrats again, to say, No Kings in our country! 

This is a RALLY for OUR GOVERNMENT TO SERVE THE PEOPLE
#### Saturday, March 28th from 10 - Noon
Corner of East Fowler Avenue &amp; North 56th Street

### Why are we doing this?

We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

Our peaceful movement is growing bigger than ever. When our families are under attack and costs are pushing people to the brink, silence is not an option. We will defend ourselves and our communities against this administration’s unjust and cruel acts of violence.

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it. Join us. We won’t back down against chaos, corruption, and cruelty.

NOW it is time to lift up your voice and join hearts &amp; hands with neighbors. 
Rain or Shine (barring hazardous conditions)
Park adjacent to former Boston Market (no parking, walking or standing in the BM lot per owner)

We will have some brief speeches at 10:00 AM and then let the chanting and music begin!! Bring a sign, your patriotic spirit and a huge voice for chanting! 

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.

Note: We will have a handicap section with chairs for those who&apos;d like to sit during the protest. You can bring your own chair or have a seat in one of ours. Look for the handicap drop-off area when you pull into the shopping center. Our parking attendants will direct you to the drop off area. 

Sign Ideas: Advocating for Immigrants, Veterans, Students, Unions &amp; Equality, Supporting Social Safety Nets &amp; American Ideals
Rejecting Nazism, hate &amp; NO ICE, No War in Iran, No Detention Centers. 

Disclaimer: This event is not endorsed or supported by the Hillsborough County Democratic Executive Committee. Participation in this event is voluntary and at your own risk. Violent or crude messaging is prohibited.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/838128/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
