        <name>Fort Myers Know Your Rights &amp; Neighborhood Safety</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Fort Myers Know Your Rights &amp; Neighborhood Safety</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 11, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This is a **Indivisible Gambit SWFL** event! Indivisible Gambit SWFL, in collaboration with the **ACLU of Florida, Florida Immigration Coalition, Unidos Immokalee, and Voices of Bonita,** is taking action, and we invite you to join us.

Across our communities, many people are *feeling anxious, uncertain, and afraid.* That reaction **is normal.** Fear is often the goal of authoritarian systems: to isolate us, silence us, and make us feel powerless. But **courage is a choice** and choosing courage together is how we protect one another and how we win.

We invite you to join us

**Saturday, April 11, 2026, 12:00–2:00 PM** for a Community Education and Organizing event at:
**Fort Myers United Church of Christ** 8210 College Pkwy, Fort Myers, FL 33919. This gathering is designed to expand our outreach and strengthen local support networks by sharing practical, life-saving information and building community capacity. Light snacks will be provided.

At this event, participants will:
Learn practical ways to stay safe and understand their rights
Recognize and respond to concerning ICE activity
Learn how volunteer legal observers educate community members and document encounters
Get involved in rapid response, neighborhood watch efforts, and mutual aid
Discover ways to support at-risk migrant families with basic needs

**Help us purchase educational materials for vulnerable communities. Donate here:**

https://secure.actblue.com/donate/indivisiblegs1413364462

We are also actively recruiting and training:
Volunteer legal observers
Rapid responders
Neighborhood watch volunteers
Community members willing to assist with mutual aid

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/920265/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
