    <Placemark>
        <name>Cathedral City ICE Protest + Food Drive</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Cathedral City ICE Protest + Food Drive</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 29, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Outside Arco/AMPM<br>67625 E Palm Canyon Dr<br>Cathedral City, CA 92234</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join our weekly #CoachellaValleyResist food drive and ICE protest in front of one of the many Coachella Valley Arco/AMPM stations owned by [local millionaire Trump megadonor Nachhattar Chandi](https://capitalandmain.com/trumps-california-henchmen-golden-state-business-enablers-0531). 

We encourage people to use the power of the purse to show that supporting oppression and secret police is not profitable! 

**Food drive for TODEC immigrant legal center!** We&apos;re collecting tortillas, beans, rice, cereal, peanut butter, hygiene products, diapers and baby wipes for [TODEC legal center](https://todec.org/).

See you there!

--------------------------------------------------------------

Our new volunteer group #CoachellaValleyResists is part of the #ResistTrump Campaign, a member of the No Kings coalition. #ResistTrump aims to achieve that via lawful, nonviolent civil resistance. Its values are Collaboration, Integrity, Nonpartisanship, and Professionalism.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/913448/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
