        <name>Biggest Little Action Group March Planning Meetings</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Biggest Little Action Group March Planning Meetings</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, March 26, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:15 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>First Congressional Church of Reno<br>627 Sunnyside Dr<br>Reno, NV 89503</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Biggest Little Action Group</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us to discuss alternatives to the usual protests. If you&apos;re tired of standing on sidewalks waving signs at cars, we plan and perform meaningful actions designed to encourage and strengthen each other in opposition to fascism.

Some actions we&apos;ve done this year include displaying portraits of the victims of ICE disappearances at the federal courthouse and at Reno&apos;s baseball stadium; creating and distributing Know Your Rights information to interstate passengers on Greyhound and Amtrak; calling for citizens to make public comment at the Board of Commissioners meeting to testify against the cooperation between ICE and the county jail; and organizing opposition to the local Republican congressman and his reluctance to hold a town hall. We&apos;re also the people responsible for displaying antifascist messages over I-80 during rush hour. Some of our individual members are involved in community defense networks like the Northern Nevada Community Defense Hotline and Court Accompaniment. We do as much as we can and welcome new ideas and new members all the time.

We are nonviolent and non-vandalizing. We work in support of democracy and the Constitution, and against the fascist actions of the Trump administration, its supporters, and its enablers. Everyone can play a role in this fight. Come and see if you like our style.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/918779/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
