<h3>Kent City Council public hearing on moratorium for detention facilities</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, April 8, 2026 at 2:00 AM UTC - 4:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>220 4th Ave S<br>Kent, WA 98032</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Kent</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The Kent City! Council passed a six-month emergency moratorium on new or expanded detention facilities (specifically targeting potential ICE detention centers) in early March 2026, with a public hearing scheduled for 7 p.m. on Tuesday, April 7, 2026, at City Hall, 220 Fourth Ave. S., to allow resident input.

Now is your time to speak out and keep this moratorium in place. 

More information can be found here: https://www.kentreporter.com/2026/03/04/kent-city-council-passes-moratorium-on-detention-centers/</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/925884/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
