        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Federal Building Fridays - Protest Trump Regime</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 27, 2026 at 6:30 PM UTC - 8:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Henry M. Jackson Federal Building<br><br>Seattle, WA 98174</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Southend Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join freedom fighters every Friday (rain or shine) for a peaceful rally in front of the Federal Building in Downtown Seattle hosted by the Troublemakers with a coalition of organizations - including Southend Indivisible - turning out our members.

We protest ICE kidnappings and terror, attacks on federal workers, gutting of the social safety net to benefit billionaires, dismantling of health care, environmental protections, research, and education, and more. We stand united against the un-American agenda of the Trump regime. Extra signs are available if you don&apos;t have one.

Want to volunteer to protect workers? Come visit the table at the event (only one!) for on-the-spot 10 minute training on canvassing businesses to help them protect their staff from ICE. You will receive all needed materials. This is organized through WA Neighborhood Defense (WAND) 
https://linktr.ee/waneighborhooddefense

For more on the Troublemakers visit troublemakerscommunity.org</p>
