<h3>NO KINGS Westminster</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Asian Village Plaza<br>9193 Bolsa Ave<br>Westminster, CA 92683</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

To the Little Saigon Community and all Defenders of Liberty:

We escaped the iron grip of communism to find refuge in the land of the free, only to witness the return of the shadows we once fled. Today, we see the &quot;ICE Gestapo&quot; and the systematic destruction of our democratic values. We see the American Dream—the very dream that gave us life—being dismantled. We see the beautiful fabric of this nation being torn apart.

We are the heirs of a nation that refused to die. Having survived the collapse of our first home, we stand now as the unbroken guardians of our second. We do not just remember the past; we use it as a shield for the American Republic. Our mission is urgent, our resolve is absolute, and our duty is clear: to ensure that the totalitarianism we fled never takes root in the soil we love. One nation lost was our tragedy. A second would be our failure. We are the memory that will not fade. We are the line that will not break. We are the Little Saigon Liberty Coalition.

Accessible restrooms
Dedicated parking spots

Notes from the organizer: Event Parking Guide 

We recommend arriving early to secure a spot. Parking is available at the following locations: Primary Parking: Asian Village Plaza. You can also park in the residential area at the corner of Alcester St. and Greenville Ave. * 

Tip: Use the pedestrian gate for a quick walk directly into the Asian Village Plaza. Nearby Plazas: Cathay Bank lot. Bolsa Plaza (accessible via Greenville Ave). Westminster Colony Plaza (please use the back lot). Overflow Parking: ABC Supermarket &amp; Bank of America (Corner of Bolsa Ave &amp; Magnolia St). Street parking along Bishop Place (behind Asian Garden Mall).

Have accessibility questions? Reply to your registration email to confirm your requirements or request more information.

Join us on March 28, 2026.

The &quot;No Kings&quot; Protest in Little Saigon, Westminster, CA

Stand for the Republic.

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904507/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
