        <name>Building an Anti-Fascist Community</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Building an Anti-Fascist Community</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 18, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Nevada County Madelyn Helling Library<br>980 Helling Way<br>Nevada City, CA 95959</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Nevada County</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Indivisible Nevada County for an engaging and interactive session exploring how communities in Minneapolis and other cities have successfully organized in response to ICE activity.

We’ll examine the tools, strategies, and tactics that helped local residents mobilize effectively and support their communities. What worked? What lessons can we learn? And how can we prepare locally if similar situations arise?

Participants will leave with a deeper understanding of how modern grassroots movements organize, the scale and coordination involved, and the practical skills that may be valuable in an uncertain political climate.</p>
