        <name>NO KINGS // Road Outrage LA</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS // Road Outrage LA</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 5:30 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Mid City LA driving loop - Culver, BH, WeHo, Silverlake, Downtown<br><br>Culver City, CA 90232</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On Saturday March 28, there will be No Kings protests all over LA – but why choose just one when you can join a bunch of them without taking a single step?
RoadOutrageLA is an organized car caravan that will do a big loop around central LA to amplify a half-dozen No Kings 3 demonstrations with our presence (and our horns). And along the way, we’ll make sure we wake up the shoppers on Rodeo Drive, shake up the tourists along Hollywood Blvd, pump up the hipsters in Silver Lake, and cheer up our immigrant neighbors in East LA.  
We’ll get the party started in a parking lot at 10AM in Culver City. We’ll have custom “NO Dictators”, “ICE Out of LA” and “No War” car flags (think Dodgers game day, but with democracy), and other stuff to make our machines the message. You can of course do your decorating at home instead and join us with your wheels ready to rock and roll; the only limitations are your creativity and traffic laws (see below). 
At 11, we’ll start rolling out a big loop, including 6 No Kings protests and busy locations along the way including:
Culver City Hall (No Kings Culver City)
	Rodeo Drive
Beverly Hills Garden Park (No Kings Beverly Hills)
	Beverly Center
West Hollywood Park (No Kings WEHO)
	Walk of Fame
N Vermont &amp; Hollywood (No Kings Hollywood)
	Silverlake
Unidad Park (No Kings Historic Fillipino Town)
	Macarthur Park
	Koreatown
        Miracle Mile
Pico &amp; La Cienega (No Kings Pico Robertson)

The whole shebang will probably take about 3 hours, but we’ll have estimated arrival times if you can’t do the whole route. 

So for No Kings 3, let’s put ourselves, and the 1st amendment, in the driver’s seat, and show that LA is united in love and resistance and we are NOT OK with this disastrous regime.

As this is a mobile event, be sure to follow all traffic laws.

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/923664/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
