        <name>ICE OUT! March to Portland Mayor’s House</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT! March to Portland Mayor’s House</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 4, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Wilshire Park<br>4116 NE 33rd Ave<br>Portland, OR 97212</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Portland Contra Las Deportaciones/Portland Against Deportations</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We&apos;re going back to the mayor&apos;s house! it&apos;s time to answer to the people!

After months of requests, we met with Mayor Keith Wilson to demand the ICE permit is revoked. We were met with abdication of responsibility, silence, and a clear commitment to keeping the ICE facility OPEN!
ICE continues to terrorize immigrants while operating out of a homebase in Portland that the city could shut down.

Portlanders have been severely gassed protesting this facility all year, and the residents of this neighborhood have experienced the serious effects of the chemicals.

If immigrants are not able to have peace at home, and if the residents of the South Waterfront neighborhood aren&apos;t able to have peace at home, neither is Mayor Keith Wilson!

That&apos;s why we&apos;re returning to protest at his home on Saturday, 4/4. We will meet and rally at Wiltshire Park and march the short walk to his house to demand he REVOKE THE ICE PERMIT!

Saturday, 4/4 12:00pm
Meet at Wilshire Park
4116 NE 33rd Ave, Portland, OR 97212</p>
