        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO ICE, NO WAR, NO TRUMP  - Honk &amp; Wave with Indivisible Oregon</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 29, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 8:15 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Northeast 21st Avenue &amp; Northeast Broadway<br>Portland, OR 97232</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Swing Left</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join your neighbors and fellow Portlanders for a family-friendly Honk &amp; Wave event. We stand united against the horrific ICE abuses and the murder of Renee Good and Alex Pretti. We reject our bully and corrupt grifter-in-chief, his spineless billionaire capitulators, and his MAGA political cronies.

And we are united in opposition to a single man using our military as his own personal army and committing this nation to war, all for his own ego.

We’re building a local movement and we need YOU! Let’s make democracy visible, energizing and show it’s worth fighting for. When we show up, we inspire others to do the same, because courage is contagious.

🗽 Bring a sign! 🗽Bring your voice! 🗽Bring your friends, kids, and neighbors!

Whether you stay for 15 minutes or the whole time, your presence counts.

🚗 Parking: available along adjacent side streets.

Indivisible Oregon is deeply committed to nonviolence as both a principle and a strategy. We strongly believe that peaceful, nonviolent activism offers social movements the most power to effect change.</p>
