        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Overpass Bannering N. Rosa Parks Way on I5</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 27, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>NE Rosa Parks Way &amp; I5 overpass<br>Portland, OR 97217</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We will be hoisting our message banners over I-5 at N. Rosa Parks Way Saturday, January 31st, 2 -3:30pm. We will also be holding up smaller signs to the local traffic on N. Rosa Parks Way. (Our overpass banners say &quot;Higher Prices? Blame Trump&quot; and &quot;ICE Kills. Blame Trump.&quot;) In addition will have an American flag (Dems are taking back the flag).

Come join us! When we show the courage to reach out to our fellow Americans with the truth, others are more likely to do the same in their own ways.

The overpass is at Exit 304 off I-5N, and the address is 1035 N. Rosa Parks Way (approximately). Street parking is available nearby and you can alternatively reach the location by bus or Yellow Line MAX, with just a few blocks of walking at the end.


*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
