        <name>No ICE Detention Centers in Oregon! Coburg</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>No ICE Detention Centers in Oregon! Coburg</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 18, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Coburg City Hall<br>91136 N Willamette St<br>Coburg, OR 97408</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Eugene - Springfield</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us in saying NO ICE CAMPS in Oregon!

The community of Newport has worked hard to push back against the Federal Government’s attempts to build an ICE Detention Center at the Newport Municipal Airport. Those efforts have resulted in a statement that &quot;ICE has no plan or intention to begin construction or open an ICE facility in the City of Newport or at Newport Municipal between now and until May 1, 2026,”

Let&apos;s help our friends in Newport tell DHS resolutely NO ICE CAMP HERE. Not now, not after May 1st, NOT EVER.

So far there are protests planned on Sat., March 14th and April 18th. Join Coburg at 12 pm in front of Coburg City Hall for a peaceful protest both days!


Cover photo be @rscherle on Instagram (faces blurred)</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/909731/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
