<h3>Queers Fight Back NO KINGS 3 March</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 6:30 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>L Street &amp; 10th Street<br>Sacramento, CA 95814</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Coalition Against Project 2025</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On No Kings Day March 28th, Sacramento, CA 

Join the Coalition Against Project 2025/Queers Fight Back! march from the Capitol to the John Moss Federal Bldg that houses ICE for a 15-minute rally then return to the Capitol for the Indivisible Sacramento Main Stage program (1 to 3 pm) and Action Zones on the L St side of the Capitol. 

We are calling for:
* The Abolition of ICE !  
* Transgender Rights !  
* Justice for the Survivors of Sexual Assault !   
* Support Labor, Support Farmworkers !  
* No Kings ! No KKK ! No Fascist USA !  

On No Kings Day, March 28:   
11:30 am: We gather at the &quot;Direct Action&quot; tents near 10th and L.  
(Optional: Join our 15 minute mini-workshop on Building Marches and Rallies: 11:40 to 11:55)  
12 pm:  March Meetup -  Capitol and 10th  
March to ICE Building, rally at N and 7th. 
12:30 pm: Return to Capitol for Indivisible Sacramento Main Stage Program 1 to 3 pm and visit Our Action Zones on the L St side


**This is not an official Indivisible Sacramento No Kings Event, but we are committed to the core principles behind all No Kings events**
  
A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.

**Official No Kings Sacramento Event Page**   
https://indivisiblesacramento.com/no-kings-rally-march-28/</p>
