<h3>ICE Out of Stockton</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Community Check-In Booth<br>621 San Juan Ave<br>Stockton, CA 95203</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Hands Off Stockton</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Did you know that Stockton has an ICE facility? Our immigrant neighbors are being kidnapped and held without due process. Join us Saturdays as we join the Community Check-in Booth to protest in solidarity with our community affected by ICE.
The CCIB is a permanent fixture committed to providing legal and community support to families in need, and make sure families come out of appointments safely. They also have a food pantry for any community member that needs it.
Please do not use mobilize to sign up for shifts at this event; this is purely to raise awareness. If you would like to sign up to volunteer, please go to tinyurl.com/icewatch209</p>
