    <Placemark>
        <name>Fairfield California 94534 and surrounding communities: ICE Out Committee</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Fairfield California 94534 and surrounding communities: ICE Out Committee</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 21, 2026 at 7:00 AM UTC - 7:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Across the country, communities are stepping up to say: ICE Out. The tide is turning, but this will only continue if we keep organizing and growing  — together. That’s why we need you.

We are calling on communities everywhere to form ICE Out groups and committees.   How? Any way that works – it could be neighbors joining neighbors, or a committee formed within an existing organization, or something entirely new. What matters is that people come together. We need to join forces to defend ourselves and one another.

ICE Out  groups and committees can work together to: 

* Push for policies that draw a bright line separating  local law enforcement from immigration enforcement, by getting ICE out of jails, ending collaboration with local police, and fighting surveillance tools like Flock cameras.

* Push for policies that create barriers to keep ICE away from  sensitive locations such as churches, schools and daycare centers.

ICE Out organizing  can also be a  line of defense, with things like:

* Safety patrols in neighborhoods or at sensitive locations.

* Constitutional observers.

* Mutual aid efforts like food delivery to immigrant families harmed by raids. 

* Any other type of direct support for people vulnerable to ICE. This work spreads love, strengthens community and resists the harm and destruction that ICE brings to our neighborhoods. 

If you are not at risk of deportation, we ask you to take action now. Be present. Be consistent. Build relationships. Show up as allies, witnesses, neighbors and friends. Stand with immigrant workers peacefully with love and care.

Remember: Solo el pueblo salva al pueblo. Only the people save the people.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/925326/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
