    <Placemark>
        <name>ICE Out of SLO County! Show Up and Speak up at the County Board Meeting</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out of SLO County! Show Up and Speak up at the County Board Meeting</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, April 7, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>SLO County Board Of Supervisors Chambers, Katcho Achadjian Government Center<br>1055 Monterey St<br>San Luis Obispo, CA 93408</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The San Luis Obispo Board of Supervisors subcommittee, including Supervisors Ortiz-Legg and Paulding along with county staff, will present a follow-up report to the January 27 TRUTH Act Forum during the regularly scheduled board meeting on April 7 at 9:00 am. The report is expected to be posted approximately a week before that with the agenda. The meeting was previously scheduled for March 24. We need to people to still show up March 24 to make sure it does not get kicked further down the road. We also request people show up in drives on April 7 to show solidarity for ICE Out of SLO County!

County staff were directed to develop measures to:

  - Exclude ICE from non-public areas of county facilities.
  - Prohibit ICE from commandeering county property for raids or detentions.
  - Require at least quarterly reporting on interactions between the Sheriff’s Office and ICE.
  - Support families affected by ICE detentions.
  - Rebuild trust within the community.

Please feel free to make comments concerning this directives prior to it at the March 24 and April 7 meetings. 

How to Provide Public Comment:

  - In Person: You may speak for up to three minutes on agenda items and three minutes during general public comment. Please fill out a speaker slip at the front or back of the chamber and submit it to the clerk.
  - Written Comment: Submit written comments by 5:00 pm the day before the meeting to ensure they are included in the agenda packet.
  - Early Comment: A regular meeting on March 24 provides an additional opportunity to provide spoken or written comments before the report is published.

Contact Information:

  - Online: Submit written comments here (https://www.slocounty.ca.gov/departments/board-of-supervisors/contact-the-board-of-supervisors)
  - Email: Boardofsups@co.slo.ca.us
  - Direct Outreach: You may also write, call, or visit individual board members directly.

We save us!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/875402/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
