        <name>Tri-Valley Signs of Solidarity: Business Canvassing</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Tri-Valley Signs of Solidarity: Business Canvassing</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 31, 2026 at 8:30 PM UTC - 10:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Koffee Time<br>618 Main Street, Suite A, Pleasanton, CA 94566<br>Pleasanton, CA 94566</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Tri-Valley</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join the Signs of Solidarity team to canvass local businesses, and ask them to post signs of support for our immigrant neighbors. 

There&apos;s been a significant increase in ICE agents entering small businesses without warrants and detaining people, including workers. It&apos;s created an environment where immigrants are often afraid to go to work or go shopping out of fear that ICE might show up. That&apos;s not how anyone in our community wants to live. Businesses should take steps to protect their workers and customers from these increasingly violent raids. 

No experience is necessary. A script is provided and a packet of signs; please bring a bag to carry them. You will receive a brief training and will be paired with an experienced canvasser. Please join us and and help to be part of the solution!

PLEASE NOTE: WE PLAN TO CANVASS IN MULTIPLE LOCATIONS IN THE TRI-VALLEY STARTING IN PLEASANTON ON JANUARY 27; HOWEVER, THE LOCATIONS WILL CHANGE WEEK TO WEEK.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/889592/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
