        <name>Indivisible Tri-Valley Immigration Meeting</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Indivisible Tri-Valley Immigration Meeting</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, April 17, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>5673 San Jose Dr<br>Pleasanton, CA 94566</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Tri-Valley</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us in Immigration Workgroup monthly meeting.

We are planning to discuss the following.

1. Success with Alameda County BOS resolutions establishing an immigration enforcement plan and ICE-free zones.  (5 min)
2. ICE Out of Dublin BOP Environmental Assessment public comment (EA expected to be circulated soon)  (10 min)
3. Create a team to drive by FCI Dublin periodically looking for evidence of construction  (10 min)
4. Establish ties to immigrant neighbors in our community.  Learn from Minnesota, be prepared for when it happens here. (10 min)
5. Adopt A Corner -  Monitor for ICE presence at Home Depot day laborers pick-up sites Do we have enough people for this?  (15 min)

We are looking forward to see you in person!</p>
