        <name>Indivisible ReSisters Contra Costa - SATURDAY PROTESTS</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Indivisible ReSisters Contra Costa - SATURDAY PROTESTS</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 5:30 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>locations throughout Contra Costa County<br>Contra Costa County, CA 94596</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible ReSisters Contra Costa</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>HERE&apos;S OUR SATURDAY PROTEST SCHEDULE. 
Always check for dates, location, time and themes each week in case something changes.  Register on this page for text reminders.
_____________________________________
       
Bring non-perishables for the food bank collection for our local community.


*** Saturday, March 28, 2026    NO KINGS 3 
Rallies and SOLIDARITY SPAN Honk &amp; Wave. Details here: https://www.indivisibleresisters.org/no-kings-3. 
Locations: Concord, Pleasant Hill, Walnut Creek
CONCORD rally starts at 10:30am
SOLIDARITY SPAN Honk &amp; Wave. 12:30 - 2 pm

********. Saturday, April 4, 2026  11:30am - 12:30pm   
Immigration Court, 1855 Gateway Blvd., CONCORD.  Meet on the sidewalk on Clayton Road side for Honk &amp; Wave. Register HERE.
Bring non-perishables for the food bank collection for our local community.  

*********. Saturday, April 11, 2026   11:30am - 12:30pm  
Liberty Bell Plaza, corner of Mt. Diablo Blvd &amp; Broadway, 
1400 Mt. Diablo Blvd., WALNUT CREEK. Rally in plaza and then march to Main St. for Honk &amp; Wave.


________________________________________________________
Saturday Protests are Indivisible events organized by Indivisible ReSisters Contra Costa. Go to IndivisibleReSisters.org for more actions and other ways to get involved. Get Saturday protest reminders via email by signing up for our weekly newsletter here:  https://secure.everyaction.com/eBsbQF1XyU6Ae2kj55KbEA2

NOTE:  We are not affiliated with the paid ballot endorsement canvassers who show up at our events. Be informed before you sign! 

These are nonviolent events. Each of us is responsible for our own conduct. Stay within your rights, don’t break laws, stay safe, stay peaceful, and avoid any risk you don’t feel comfortable with. Don’t obstruct traffic, protest inside any business, impede people from entering or exiting any property, or commit any acts of property damage. Ignore any counter protestors and stay focused on peacefully delivering our message. If you need help or see something troubling, tell a uniformed police officer or call 911. If you can safely do so, record troublesome behavior with your phone, as this is often a strong deterrent to bad behavior.

WHISTLES - A COMMUNITY SAFETY UPDATE
We love everyone&apos;s enthusiasm with their various noise-makers but note that whistles are now used for ICE warnings. In order to avoid undue fear, confusion or panic for our communities, please refrain from using whistles hereafter for any protest events.  Bells and horns are alternatives. 

By attending or participating in this event, you acknowledge that media outlets and event partners’ members may capture and use photos or videos taken during the event. This includes content of individuals, booths, or businesses, as well as publicly shared posts, for promotional purposes across digital and print platforms. No additional permissions or compensation will be provided.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/860942/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
