        <name>Join Our Sign Making Party for No Kings 3!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Join Our Sign Making Party for No Kings 3!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 27, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>5487 Canary Rd<br>Florence, OR 97439</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>WHAT: Sign Making Party for No Kings 3
​WHEN: Friday, March 27, 11 am - 1 pm
​WHERE:  [Google Maps link]
Honeyman State Park, West Woahink Recreational Meeting Hall, 
5487 Canary Rd, Florence, OR 97439
To make No Kings 3 a community-building event, we are hosting a Sign Making Party (using our Power to the Peasants theme from No Kings 2) the day before the rally, on Friday March 27. In support of our immigrant community now under siege by ICE, we have titled it &apos;Power to the Peasants Celebrates Immigrants&apos;.

So come and gather with fellow democracy defenders for a Mexican themed event with food, music, and a chance to create signs for the nationwide rally. Locally, the No Kings 3 rally is taking place in Florence on Saturday, March 28 from 1-2 pm on the east side of US Route 101, from the intersection with OR 126, south to Florence City Hall at 1st St.

Live music by Box Rat will be on hand to entertain us!


*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
