    <Placemark>
        <name>NO KINGS Street Fest (Palo Alto)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS Street Fest (Palo Alto)</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>El Camino Real from Embarcadero to California Avenue<br>Embarcadero Road &amp; El Camino Real<br>Palo Alto, CA 94306</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Palo Alto Plus</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>_Music! Protest! Community!_ Join us for a street festival on No Kings Day where together we will lift our spirits and claim our power. We will **sing and dance**. We will **raise our signs**—and our voices. We will **connect with our neighbors**. In defiance of the kingly pretensions of Donald Trump and his authoritarian regime, we will **celebrate our rights **as democratic citizens.

Make your way on March 28 to El Camino Real in Palo Alto.

- Listen to **local bands** and join a &quot;resistance rock&quot; singalong

- Bring **protest signs** and wave to passing cars

- Visit **activity areas** devoted to celebrating our freedoms

[Learn more about the No Kings Street Fest!](https://nokingspaloalto.org)

What began in 2025 as a single day of defiance has become a sustained national resistance to tyranny, spreading from small towns to city centers and across every community in America (and beyond). On March 28—**the third No Kings Day**—rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: _No thrones. No crowns. No kings._

El Camino Real is also known as “the King’s Highway.” But on this day, thousands of us will turn the street into the **No Kings Highway**. 

Street Fest activities will take place on El Camino Real from **Embarcadero Road to California Avenue** between 2:00 PM and 4:00 PM. Sidewalk protest will be welcome in that area, and across all of El Camino. _Bring your best sign! Wear a costume!_

Come together and celebrate American freedom—the freedom to say:

- No to war on Iran

- No to ICE brutality

- No to deportation camps

- No to mass surveillance

- No to voter suppression

- No to Epstein Class predators

- No to attacks on science, education, and healthcare

The No Kings Street Fest in Palo Alto is part of Peninsula Out in Force, a multi-group effort to rally people across the San Francisco Peninsula—from Sunnyvale up to San Mateo—in a celebration of American freedom and a rejection of MAGA tyranny. In many cities and over many miles, Peninsula residents will be convening on El Camino Real between 2:00 PM and 4:00 PM. [Learn more.](https://www.indivisiblepeninsulabayarea.org)

Organized by [Indivisible Palo Alto Plus](https://indivisiblepaloaltoplus.org/) and [It’s Blue Turn](https://itsblueturn.com/).

_A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events._</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/911213/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
