        <name>A Whistle and a Cell Phone. The only weapons I own.</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>A Whistle and a Cell Phone. The only weapons I own.</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, April 7, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 6:45 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>In solidarity with Unitarian Universalists’, Faith Leaders, Everyone in Minneapolis, the United States, and the World,
The Witticists hosts Drop-In Virtual Peace Events
Ongoing Virtual Events - Join from Anywhere. 
Tuesdays, Jan 27, Feb 10, and Mar 10 - from 11:00 am - 11:45 am

Drop-In Anytime during the scheduled hours,
and stay as long as you can.
Peace Rally Let’s Talk humbly, thoughtfully, about what’s happening in Minneapolis and our local communities. Make good noise. Bring a whistle, or improvise.

“On Friday, January 23, Minnesotans of every race, place, and faith gathered across the state in prayer vigils for a Day of Truth and Freedom.
It was a statewide day of non-violent moral action, reflection: no work, no school, no shopping — only community, conscience, and collective action.

“The clergy call and gathering on the 22nd was intended to amplify and support the demands of 1/23:
1. ICE must leave Minnesota immediately.
2. The officer who killed Renee Good must be held legally accountable.
3. No additional federal funding for ICE in the upcoming Congressional budget and ICE should be investigated for human and Constitutional violations of Americans and our neighbors.
4. We call upon Minnesota and national companies to become 4th Amendment businesses, cease economic relations with ICE, and refuse ICE entry or using their property for staging grounds.
Visit ICE Out Now MN and May Day Strong for more information.”
It was a statewide day of non-violent moral action, reflection.
There was a unified, statewide pause in daily economic activity. Instead, Minnesotans spent time with family, neighbors, and their community to show Minnesota’s moral heart and collective economic power. 

WITTicists “We’re In This Together”
Georgette deBlois, host, is passionate about social issues and pro-education, choice, diversity, and LGBTQ+. In March of 2025, Randy Jones  joined with her to form an online political discussion group called the WITTicists, WITT being an acronym for We’re In This Together. In October 2025, we were invited to be an &quot;Indivisible&quot; Group. We host virtual and attend in-person rallies to break the yoke of disinformation and misinformation, and with peaceful, no-nonsense, loud voices, declare allegiance to the Constitution and the Protection of Our Democracy

This a local Indivisible event

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/890966/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
