        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Sunrise Bay Area: Post-No King’s Day Mixer [SF]</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>San Francisco City Hall<br>1 Dr Carlton B Goodlett Pl<br>San Francisco, CA 94102</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Sunrise Movement</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Do you keep asking yourself - “what does marching at events like no kings day do?” Do you get hyped marching and chanting only to go home feeling like you didn’t accomplish anything? Does ice, trump and his cronies, even the democratic party, make you so damn maddd that you’d do ANYTHING to be apart of bringing the authoritarianism to an end?

Well look no further than partying post no kings day with the coolest people. We’re Sunrise Movement Bay Area, a youth-led movement out to end ice, end billionaire rule, and get the flock out of Oakland and San Francisco!

Stop by to chat and plug in to how we will win and truly make difference! Revolution starts with us.

Location TBD so stay tuned.</p>
