    <Placemark>
        <name>Love as Action: Resisting Authoritarianism with a Memorial Meeting for Worship</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Love as Action: Resisting Authoritarianism with a Memorial Meeting for Worship</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 25, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Golden Gate Park - Remember When (Love Blocks)<br>244 John F Kennedy Dr<br>San Francisco, CA 94117</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> AFSC Quaker Engagement</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p># Love as Action: Resisting Authoritarianism
## Bearing Witness, Building Hope

### Quaker public witness has stood in opposition to cruel and authoritarian actions in our country before. It is time for us to show this love in action again. 

Please join the American Friends Service Committee and San Francisco Friends to bear witness and show resistance to the authoritarian actions in our country. 

On Saturday April 25 at 2:00pm we will gather at the Remember When (Love Blocks) in Golden Gate Park for one hour of silent public worship.

Who Are We?

We are with the San Francisco Friends Meeting (Quakers), a spiritual community committed to peace, equality, and justice. Our faith calls us to live with integrity and compassion, and to act for a world where every person is treated with dignity.

Why Are We Here?

We are holding a Memorial Meeting for Worship — essentially, a Quaker funeral service — for all those who have died in ICE custody or been killed by ICE brutality. We invite anyone who wishes to join us in this act of public witness against fear, violence, and authoritarianism — and in solidarity with communities facing harm and dehumanization. By standing together in silence, we affirm that every person has worth, that fear and violence must give way to love and fairness, and that our communities thrive when all are welcomed. And taking action publicly is a visible commitment to justice and compassion.

What Is Quaker Worship?

Quaker worship is a communal time of silent, expectant waiting. We gather without clergy or sermons, just open hearts and minds, listening for the inward presence of the Spirit.

- Silent and Centered: We begin in stillness, seeking divine guidance.

- Open to All: Anyone may join us in this quiet space.

- Speaking into the Silence: If someone feels deeply led, they may share a brief message for the spiritual nurture of the group. Silence continues between messages for reflection.

To find our more about Love as Action nationally and get more resources visit us at [afsc.org/love-action](www.afsc.org/love-action)</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/914990/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
