        <name>NO KINGS Reykjavik ICELAND - **15:00-18:00 GMT**</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS Reykjavik ICELAND - **15:00-18:00 GMT**</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Austurvöllur, 101 Pósthússtræti, 101 Reykjavik Iceland<br>101 Pósthússtræti, 101 Reykjavik Iceland<br> 96950</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

Every day seems to bring with it a fresh wave of incomprehensible horrors delivered straight to the small, bright rectangles we carry around in our pockets. Perhaps the most cancerous of these horrors is the creeping growth of anti-immigrant and anti-refugee rhetoric, which appears to be making a comfortable home for itself in the very soul of the world’s liberal democracies.

Although it is our duty as citizens of the world to maintain awareness of The Horrors, we must also actively seek out The Joy. Joy is both the guiding light in the dark and a subversive act of resistance. Joy reminds us of the things worth fighting for and gives us hope for a world that can be, rather than despair at the world that is. As we navigate a western society that does its best to break us down we must take radical action to preserve joy at all costs.

To that end, please join Indivisible Iceland for No Kings 3.0 on Saturday, 28 March 2026, a celebration of Iceland’s mosaic of immigrants from all over the world and an exercise in community-building. 

You will find us at Austurvöllur from 15:00 to 18:00. Immigrants, refugees, and all allies thereof are welcome for an afternoon of music, dancing, joy, and human connection.

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/921313/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
