        <name>NO KINGS! Overpass Bannering- Wed Thurs  Fri &amp; Sat</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS! Overpass Bannering- Wed Thurs  Fri &amp; Sat</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 25, 2026 at 11:30 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Portland Metro - Coordinated Overpasses I-5, 205, 405, 217, 84,212<br>Locations W Th Fri eve rush &amp; Sat am.  Listed below. Sign up<br>Portland 97232</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Portland Metro Indivisible Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>### Join  a NO KINGS Overpass
#### Afternoon Rush Hour Wed 3/25, Thur 3/26, Fri 3/27 and Saturday Morning 3/28

Join one of these organized Overpass Groups, union locals, students, clubs, neighbors, congregations; every overpass needs 10-20 people to hold banners, signs, flags, wave. Many of our volunteers have been doing these visibility actions, and can support additional teams taking over all the spots

We&apos;re part of the Mexico to Canada Bridge Banner Challenge In the Portland Metro, we&apos;ll share the No Kings message over I-5, 205, 84, 26, 212 

Bring US Flags to wave, also pompoms, Wear your Frog and Chicken suits, Really big signs ( Each letter needs to be 18&quot; tall to be read from the road.)  Raingear, snacks and water.  Themes - NO KINGS, NO WAR, ICE Out, Tyrants Be Dammed, Workers R United, Neighbors R United, No Fear, All The People 

**Checkback through event day - we&apos;re adding locations all the time.**
**Locations - Wed 3/25 4:30pm**

- 205 at Monterey

- 205 at Sunnyside

**Locations - Thursday 3/26 4pm**

- I-5 Rosa Parks Way

- I-5 at North Skidmore Street &amp; North Michigan Avenue

- 84 53rd Ave  Northeast Hoyt &amp; Northeast 53rd

- 205 at Market St

**Locations Friday 3/27 4pm**

- I-5 Bryant St Bridge

- I-5 Rosa Parks Way

- I-5 Gibbs St Pedestrian Bridge

- I-5 Terwilliger Blvd &amp; SW Barbur  3 pm

- 405 1st St

- 205 at Market St

- 84 at 238th/Wood Village

**Locations Saturday 3/28 10am**

- I-5 Bryant St Bridge

- I-5 Terwilliger Blvd &amp; SW Barbur 

- 405 1st St

- 84 at Earl Blumenaur Bridge ( by 7th &amp; Lloyd)

- 205 at Market St

- 26 at Skyline  Sylvan  Noon-2

- 26 at 185th  in Tanasbourne

- Hwy 99 at Bybee 

- Hwy 99 at Tacoma

- 212 at Foster in Damascus 11am 

- 212 at US 26 E, Boring, 4pm


**Do you want to cover another location? Contact Portland Metro Indivisible Network at portlandmetroindnetwork@gmail.com for more details and to coordinate messages. Let&apos;s do this together!**

We banner on overpasses that are easily and safely accessed by surface streets. All participants agree to stay on the sidewalk/ out of the roadway behind the fences.. 


A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it. Join us.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/922842/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
