    <Placemark>
        <name>PETITION: Stop Secret Deportations and Stand for Due Process in America</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>PETITION: Stop Secret Deportations and Stand for Due Process in America</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, May 17, 2025 at 4:00 AM UTC - 4:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Mississippi Democratic Party</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>They say this is the land of the free—but in today’s America, people are being taken from their homes and communities without warning, without a lawyer, and without even a phone call.

Right now, under this administration, ICE agents are rounding up men, women, and even children—some of them U.S. citizens—without proper identification, without cause, and without any concern for our rights as Americans. 

They’re skipping courts. They’re skipping judges. They’re putting people on planes and shipping them out like they don’t matter.

This isn’t law and order. This is government overreach. And it’s not how things are supposed to work in a country that calls itself free.

We know what it’s like down here in Mississippi. We know what it feels like to be ignored, mistreated, and pushed to the side. Now ICE is doing the same to our neighbors, our church members, our coworkers, and our friends.

Nobody should be dragged off in the night with no hearing, no lawyer, no phone call.

Whether someone’s lived here ten years or ten generations, they deserve a fair shot. That’s just basic justice—and the kind of freedom our country is supposed to stand for.

Sign this petition and tell our elected leaders:

We want ICE held accountable. We want due process respected. And we won’t stand for secret deportations in our communities.

This is our home, and we’re not letting fear take it from us.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/791295/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
