        <name>Signs of Solidarity in Yakima Valley</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Signs of Solidarity in Yakima Valley</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 12, 2026 at 8:00 AM UTC - 7:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Central Washington Resistance</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Central Washington Resistance is organizing Signs of Solidarity in Yakima, which was created because the Trump administration is deploying ICE deep into the hearts of our communities in an effort to spread fear among immigrants. Many immigrant families – even citizens – are terrified to go to work, to do their shopping, or to go about their lives for fear they may be rounded up by unaccountable masked men. 

We can and must stand up for immigrants and show that they are essential and welcomed members of our communities.

We will be visiting local businesses in our neighborhoods, asking business owners or managers to post signs that declare their support for their immigrant neighbors and opposition to ICE as well as create a private area for employees that ICE cannot legally enter without a signed judicial warrant. These are simple steps that businesses can take to protect their employees from ICE and make all immigrants feel welcome in your community.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/903211/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
