        <name>Hoosiers Warn Chicago Bears and other businesses to stay clear of ICE in Indiana</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Hoosiers Warn Chicago Bears and other businesses to stay clear of ICE in Indiana</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, March 5, 2026 at 5:00 AM UTC - 4:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Bears In Illinois: Bears Stay Clear of ICE in Indiana</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>If you live in Indiana, we ask you to sign this petition to keep the Chicago Bears in Illinois and prevent them from moving to Indiana.  By moving to Indiana, Chicago Bears&apos; fans would be vulnerable to the cruel and inhumane practices currently in the Hoosier state. ***We are asking people to sign this petition for the Chicago Bears to stay away from relocating to Indiana so that they do not reward the Hoosier state&apos;s harmful immigration policies in Indiana.*** 

Gov. Braun recently signed a new bill to try to lure the Chicago Bears to Hammond, IN (on February 26, 2026). ***In addition, Gov. Braun is on the verge of signing SB76 THIS WEEK (as of March 5, 2026).**** SB76 is a restrictive and harmful immigration bill that will have severe ripple effects for children and families throughout Indiana.

***An entity like the Chicago Bears franchise should be wise enough to not fall for the bait proposed by Indiana legislators.*** The Bears should stay in their home state of Illinois. DO NOT invest in a state this is actively passing unconstitutional anti-immigrant bills and spending more money in growing its immigrant detention centers.

We especially ask the Chicago Bears not to support a state whose legislators are keen causing more harm than good to all Americans. Previous states who have passed anti-immigrant bills like Indiana’s SB76 have lost billions of dollars due to people/corporations/businesses refusing to set foot in harmful immigration states. SB76 is similar to bills that have left similar states entrenched in lawsuits (as seen with SB1070 in Arizona with former Gov. Jan Brewer in 2010, SB4 in Texas with Gov. Greg Abbott, SB1718 and SB 4-C in Florida with Gov. Ron DeSantis). 

**Given the severity of SB76, the ACLU of Indiana has stepped in. The American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) of Indiana is concerned that Indiana&apos;s SB76 violates the Fourth Amendment by increasing the risk of unlawful detention and unreasonable seizure. The bill threatens to violate rights by causing individuals to be incarcerated longer than necessary, even with proof of citizenship, and encourages racial profiling.** 

**WE ARE ASKING THE Chicago Bears (and future business/corporations) to NOT support/invest in a state that is actively harming immigrant and Hoosier residents alike.**

DO NOT allow the Bears to be lured into a state that is inviting ICE agents to appear unannounced in K-12 schools and universities. There is no due process in immigration enforcement practices in Indiana with its newest proposed laws. Indiana is pouring billions into growing its for-profit immigrant detention centers, which is the complete opposite of what Illinois has done for immigrants. Don&apos;t allow the Bears to turn a BLIND EYE to the inhumane treatment of immigrants and Americans throughout the state of Indiana. Hold our Indiana legislators and governor accountable, and do not let them win the bidding war for the Chicago Bears stadium relocation in Hammond, IN. 

***We are asking the Bears NOT to move to Indiana because they would reward and support a state that is:
1.) actively inviting ICE agents into our CHILDREN&apos;S K-12 schools and universities, 
2.) actively violating the constitutional rights of lawful citizens and immigrants being racially profiled, and 
3.) expanding immigration detention centers to house nearly 2,000-3,000+ immigrant detainees per day in for-profit detention centers throughout the state.***

**HOW YOU CAN TAKE ACTION:**

**1.) Sign this petition to show Indiana stakeholders YOU DO NOT support their efforts to lure the Chicago Bears while simultaneously harming immigrants and citizens in Indiana!**

**2.) Call AND email AND tag the listed legislators and executives everyday until the Bears relocation decision is finalized. TAKE SCREENSHOTS of the people you&apos;ll call and email below LOCATED NEAR THE end of the petition details. **

**3.) Forward this petition to 10 friends!**


***The most problematic changes within SB76:****
(1) enforcement has broadened to all levels, including federal, state and local law enforcement; 
(2) there is now a $10,000 civil penalty for K-12 schools and universities that knowingly or intentionally refuse to comply; 
(3) SB76 also establishes penalties for employers who knowingly hire unauthorized aliens and provides legal protection for government officials sued for immigration enforcement actions, and 
(4) The legislation removes the mens rea (intent) standard, making it harder to sue entities for wrongful detention, as the focus is on compliance with federal requests.

**SB76 does NOT DO ENOUGH to protect citizens and law-abiding immigrants against immigration enforcement.** Because it is such a proactive enforcement mechanism, there will be many citizens, legal permanent residents and law-abiding immigrants who are subject to immigration enforcement practices that should not be. 

Under SB76, if you are wrongfully involved in an immigration enforcement process, you can’t sue under this new bill. Americans can’t argue and sue on the grounds of being wrongfully detained. The removal of &quot;mens rea&quot; (intent) standard, makes it harder to sue entities for wrongful detention--which is a major threat to our civil liberties as Americans!

CHILDREN in K-12 schools in Indiana are set to be harmed and traumatized by SB76. Schools (churches, hospitals and universities) should be safe places. Schools in large urban cities are the primary district targeted by Indiana Senate Bill 76. SB76 restricts how schools can handle federal immigration enforcement. SB 76 would allow federal immigration officials (ICE) greater access to public school property. ICE agents can show up announced, without any need to reach out to school officials.

If the Chicago Bears were to move to Indiana, this would support the increasing lawlessness and unconstitutional overreach of ICE enforcement operations in Indiana. Gov. Braun has plans to expand 3 detention center spaces in Indiana, a move which is the complete opposite of what we have seen in Illinois.  In Indiana, Gov. Braun has invested $15.8 billion dollars to the Speedway Slammer (Miami Correctional Facility) and there are plans to spend more in additional detention centers. 

Pressure the stakeholders involved in the Bears relocation package. Contact the following legislators and business executives after signing this petition. Again, the Chicago Bears (and future business/corporations) should not support a state that is actively harming immigrant and Hoosier residents alike.


**TAKE SCREENSHOTS OF THE EXECUTIVE LEADERS YOU CAN CALL/EMAIL**


**Sportscorp LTD**
(Chicago-based, sports consulting firm involved in relocation)
(Marc Ganis is leading relocation plans)
Phone: (312) 649-9200

**Chicago Bears**
Email contact form: https://www.chicagobears.com/about/contact-us
[We are asking the Chicago Bears to stay in Illinois so as to protects its legacy, stand with immigrants and protect fans from harmful immigration policies like SB76 in Indiana. DO NOT invest in a state this is actively passing unconstitutional anti-immigrant bills and spending more money in growing its immigrant detention centers. Gov. Braun in Indiana is about to sign SB76 into law THIS WEEK. In the long run, the BEARS have more to LOSE than to GAIN from moving to Indiana.]

**LEADERSHIP IN INDIANA STATEHOUSE**:

Urge them to have Gov. Braun VETO SB76 this week and pull investments from immigration detention centers throughout the state. We are set to lose massive investments, including but not limited to, the Chicago Bears&apos; relocation. Unconstitutional, discriminatory and unlawful anti-immigrant practices like that seen in SB 76 and in Indiana’s growing detention centers are costly in the long-run and they tarnish our state reputation.

**District 1 - Frank J. Mrvan (Democrat)** 
(based in Hammond, IN, where new stadium plans are proposed)
@RepMrvan
IN Office Phone: (219) 795-1844
DC Office Phone: (202) 225-2461
Email contact form https://mrvan.house.gov/contact


**Governor Braun (R)**
Phone: 317-232-4567
@GovBraun
Share an opinion: https://in.accessgov.com/gov/Forms/Page/gov/share-an-opinion/1 

**District 7 - U.S. House Rep. Andre Carson (Democrat)**
Phone: (317) 283-6516
@CongressmanAndreCarson
Email: andre.carson07@mail.house.gov

**Senator Jim Banks (R)** 
(has office staff in Fort Wayne, Hammond and D.C.)
@SenatorJimBanks
IN Office Phone: (260) 321-7130
DC Office Phone: (202) 224-4814
Email form: https://www.banks.senate.gov/contact/share-your-opinion/

**Senator Todd Young (R)**
@SenatorToddYoung
IN Office Phone: (317) 226-6700
DC Office Phone: (202) 224-5623
Email form: https://www.young.senate.gov/contact/email-todd/</p>
