        <name>South Asians Demand an Immediate End to Lawless ICE Violence</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>South Asians Demand an Immediate End to Lawless ICE Violence</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 25, 2026 at 5:00 AM UTC - 4:59 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> SAAVE Texas</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This is no longer political. It is a constitutional and moral crisis.
SAMPLE SCRIPT 

Hi, my name is [NAME], and I’m a South Asian constituent from [CITY, ZIP].

I’m calling because I am deeply concerned about the direction of this country. This is no longer politics — it is a moral, ethical, and constitutional crisis.

We have now witnessed two Americans, Renee Good and Alex Pretti, shot and killed by federal immigration agents, while countless others are dying in detention without ever having their day in court.

Armed, often unidentified agents are approaching South Asian families without warrants, without transparency, and without accountability. The line between constitutional law and unchecked force is being erased.

We demand that you act immediately to stop ICE’s lawless violence, defend constitutional protections, and refuse to fund abuse.

Texas is home to one of the largest South Asian populations in the country, and our communities are watching closely.

I demand that Senator Cornyn oppose any funding that expands ICE and push for immediate accountability and strict constitutional limits on enforcement.

OTHER DETAILS TO SHARE 
Congress must stop ICE now and defend the Constitution
South Asian communities are in deep fear and alarm as armed, often unidentified agents approach families without warrants, without transparency, and without accountability. The line between lawful enforcement and unchecked violence is being erased, and constitutional protections are being dangerously blurred.

We have now witnessed two Americans shot and killed by federal immigration agents, while countless others have died in detention without ever having their day in court. This breakdown of due process and rule of law threatens every community.

Texas is home to one of the largest South Asian populations in the country, and our families are watching closely.

We demand immediate action to stop ICE’s lawless violence, defend constitutional rights, and refuse to fund abuse.

Join us in calling Senators Cruz and Cornyn to demand accountability, constitutional protections, and an end to this crisis.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/893369/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
