    <Placemark>
        <name>Students Belong in the Classroom: ICE Out of Our Communities</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Students Belong in the Classroom: ICE Out of Our Communities</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, March 26, 2026 at 10:30 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> United We Dream Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>All across the country, students are standing together, exercising their first amendment rights, and walking out of their classrooms to send a clear message: our immigrant neighbors, classmates, and families belong here.

Students belong in the classroom. We shouldn&apos;t have to feel afraid to hide who we are, where we come from, or what language we speak at home. We believe in a future where every student has a right to feel safe and supported by their community. 

**Join UWD and UWDA on March 26th, for a community call where we’ll come together, know our rights as students, and explore how we can stand up for ourselves and each other through peaceful protest, like walkouts.** Whether you’ve never organized anything before or you’ve done it a hundred times, we’ll walk you through the tips, tools, and guidance you need to decide how you want to show up for your community.

On the call, we&apos;ll:

- 🫂 Come together and make meaning of this moment
- ⌛ Explore the historical power of student-led movements
- 🧰 Share a suggestions toolkit on how YOU can choose to exercise your First Amendment rights, including organizing a walkout
- ✊ Connect with other students across the country fighting for our immigrant communities

We are the generation that takes care of each other and this is our moment to prove it.

*You do not have to be 18 to attend!*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/914102/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
]]></description>
