        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Phone bank with Team Waz!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 27, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> John Waz for State House (OR Working Families Party)</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We&apos;re hoping to call every voter we want to reach within the month of March-- and we can&apos;t do it without you! These are REALLY easy calls to friendly neighbors. Join us every Thursday evening for a quick training and then some calls in to voters in SW Portland and Lake Oswego.

Waz is a middle school teacher running in District 38 because working families need representation in Salem. He wants to make sure that our community is safe from ICE, makes education a priority, and that we make housing and affordability a priority! And he&apos;s the only candidate challenging an incumbent in the primary.

Find out more about the campaign by following us @wazfororegon!</p>
