        <name>Statewide Organizing Working Group</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Statewide Organizing Working Group</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 30, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> New York Working Families Party</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>From Onondaga County to New York City, the Working Families Party secured historic electoral wins this November -- and now the work has only just begun. The Trump Administration has slashed funding for critical services like SNAP and Medicaid, dumped millions of tax payer dollars into ICE, and is gearing up to cut more and more from our budget. New York State has the power and responsibility to STEP UP during the 2026 state budget and make the ultra wealthy pay their fare share so that we can fund the programs and services that allow NYers to thrive. Universal childcare, affordable housing, a true living wage, affordable and accessible healthcare are all possible and on the horizon for NYS. 

But we need YOU 🫵 to win.

Join us on Mondays at 6pm from January through April to build statewide power and directly contribute to NY WFP&apos;s strategy to advance policies that address the deep rooted economic inequalities in our state. 

Come ready to: lead virtual/in-person field events, sharpen your strategic decision making skills, deepen our collective political education, and meet likeminded volunteers across NYS.

NO PRIOR EXPERIENCE NECESSARY!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/884183/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-03-25T07:02:17.763Z</i></p>
