        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NDLON Rapid Response Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, April 22, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 8:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join the National Day Laborer Organizing Network for a national training to discuss key strategies for Rapid Response in the case of ICE activity in your community.

What to expect: 

* Basic protocols for Rapid Response.

* Instructions on what to do if ICE shows up at your local day labor corner or in your neighborhood.

* Information pertaining to your rights as an observer and more.

This effort is part of a broader campaign led by NDLON to support workers, build grassroots power, and transform our communities from the ground up. 

We’re looking forward to connecting with all of you. Let’s keep building, together.

— The NDLON Organizing Team</p>
